{"type":"text","timestamp":1775865999681,"sessionID":"ses_28623daf0ffez95ulaFqw2gZJI","part":{"id":"prt_d79dcaee9001JK7JMtGalRFJCi","messageID":"msg_d79dc95560011QF1YDgNqqDzH0","sessionID":"ses_28623daf0ffez95ulaFqw2gZJI","type":"text","text":"Now I understand the structure. I need to add AR-025 — MetadataService 与数据模型 to the design.md file. Let me append the new section.","time":{"start":1775865999678,"end":1775865999678}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775866000766,"sessionID":"ses_28623daf0ffez95ulaFqw2gZJI","part":{"id":"prt_d79dcb140001annf2ZCWe87mEg","messageID":"msg_d79dc95560011QF1YDgNqqDzH0","sessionID":"ses_28623daf0ffez95ulaFqw2gZJI","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_0a4f6a68d1ca4e449a3a081b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md","offset":1180},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1180: - **WHEN** the user passes `--version` (eager option, `Optional[bool]`, default `None`)\n1181: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print `AgentCube CLI (kubectl agentcube) version: {__version__}` (Rich markup) and exit without running a subcommand (`typer.Exit()`), where `__version__` is `0.1.0` from `agentcube.__init__`\n1182: \n1183: ##### Scenario: Global verbose logging\n1184: - **GIVEN** the user passes `--verbose` / `-v` (`bool`, default `False`) on the root callback\n1185: - **WHEN** the callback runs\n1186: - **THEN** the system SHALL call `logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)`\n1187: \n1188: #### Requirement: `pack` command\n1189: The system SHALL provide `pack` to validate and prepare a workspace, merge CLI overrides into metadata, optionally generate a `Dockerfile`, and report paths.\n1190: \n1191: ##### Scenario: Options and defaults\n1192: - **GIVEN** the user runs `pack`\n1193: - **WHEN** options are omitted\n1194: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL use: `workspace` = `\".\"` (`-f` / `--workspace`, `str`); `agent_name` = `None` (`--agent-name`, `Optional[str]`); `language` = `None` (`--language`); `entrypoint` = `None` (`--entrypoint`); `port` = `None` (`--port`, `Optional[int]`); `build_mode` = `None` (`--build-mode`); `description` = `None` (`--description`); `output` = `None` (`--output`); `verbose` = `False` (`--verbose`, command-local)\n1195: \n1196: ##### Scenario: Successful pack\n1197: - **GIVEN** a valid workspace path\n1198: - **WHEN** `pack` completes without exception\n1199: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print success with `agent_name`, resolved `workspace_path`, and `metadata_path` (reported as `{final_workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml`), using a Rich `Progress` spinner during work\n1200: \n1201: ##### Scenario: Pack failure handling\n1202: - **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack` raises\n1203: - **WHEN** `verbose` is `True`\n1204: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print `Error packaging agent: {e}` in red, print a full traceback, and exit with code `1`\n1205: \n1206: #### Requirement: `build` command\n1207: The system SHALL build a container image from a packaged workspace using local Docker when `build_mode` is `local` (default in metadata), with optional proxy and tag derived from metadata version.\n1208: \n1209: ##### Scenario: Options and defaults\n1210: - **GIVEN** the user runs `build`\n1211: - **WHEN** options are omitted\n1212: - **THEN** defaults SHALL be: `workspace` = `\".\"` (`-f` / `--workspace`); `proxy` = `None` (`-p` / `--proxy`); `cloud_provider` = `None` (`--cloud-provider`); `output` = `None` (`--output`); `verbose` = `False` (`--verbose`)\n1213: \n1214: ##### Scenario: Local Docker build prerequisites\n1215: - **GIVEN** `build_mode` resolves to `local`\n1216: - **WHEN** Docker is unavailable\n1217: - **THEN** `BuildRuntime` SHALL raise `RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")` surfaced via CLI error handling\n1218: \n1219: ##### Scenario: Version increment on build\n1220: - **GIVEN** a successful local build path\n1221: - **WHEN** `BuildRuntime.build` runs\n1222: - **THEN** the system SHALL increment `metadata.version` (patch bump for `X.Y.Z`, or append `.1` / fallback `{version}-1`) before build and revert the version in metadata if build fails\n1223: \n1224: #### Requirement: `publish` command\n1225: The system SHALL publish/deploy using provider `agentcube` (AgentRuntime CR) or `k8s` (Deployment + NodePort Service), preparing the image via Docker push or explicit image URL as implemented in `PublishRuntime`.\n1226: \n1227: ##### Scenario: Options and defaults\n1228: - **GIVEN** the user runs `publish`\n1229: - **THEN** defaults SHALL include: `workspace` = `\".\"`; `version` = `None` (`--version`); `image_url` = `None` (`--image-url`); `image_username` = `None` (`--image-username`); `image_password` = `None` (`--image-password`); `description` = `None`; `region` = `None` (`--region`); `cloud_provider` = `None`; `provider` = `\"agentcube\"` (`--provider`); `node_port` = `None` (`--node-port`, `Optional[int]`); `replicas` = `None` (`--replicas`); `namespace` = `None` (`--namespace`); `verbose` = `False`\n1230: \n1231: ##### Scenario: AgentCube provider prerequisites\n1232: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `agentcube`\n1233: - **WHEN** metadata lacks `router_url` or `workload_manager_url`\n1234: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message requiring both fields in `agent_metadata.yaml`\n1235: \n1236: ##### Scenario: Standard Kubernetes publish flow\n1237: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `k8s` and Kubernetes client initializes\n1238: - **WHEN** publish proceeds\n1239: - **THEN** the system SHALL call `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent`, then `wait_for_deployment_ready(..., timeout=120)`, updating metadata with deployment info; on readiness failure it SHALL raise `RuntimeError` after recording error in metadata\n1240: \n1241: #### Requirement: `invoke` command\n1242: The system SHALL POST JSON to the published agent endpoint, parse `--payload` as JSON, merge optional `--header` entries, and for AgentRuntime CR deployments rewrite the URL to `{base}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/` when `k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\"`.\n1243: \n1244: ##### Scenario: Options and defaults\n1245: - **GIVEN** the user runs `invoke`\n1246: - **THEN** defaults SHALL be: `workspace` = `\".\"`; `payload` = `\"{}\"` (`--payload`, `str`); `header_list` = `None` (`--header`, repeatable `List[str]`); `provider` = `\"agentcube\"`; `verbose` = `False`\n1247: \n1248: ##### Scenario: Invalid payload\n1249: - **GIVEN** `payload` is not valid JSON\n1250: - **WHEN** the command parses it\n1251: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print invalid JSON in red and exit with code `1` (before `_handle_error`)\n1252: \n1253: ##### Scenario: Invalid header format\n1254: - **GIVEN** a header string without a single `:` separator\n1255: - **WHEN** headers are parsed\n1256: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print expected `key:value` format and exit with code `1`\n1257: \n1258: ##### Scenario: Session header on invoke\n1259: - **GIVEN** metadata contains `session_id`\n1260: - **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime.invoke` runs\n1261: - **THEN** the HTTP client SHALL add header `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` (same spelling as response handling) to the request\n1262: \n1263: #### Requirement: `status` command\n1264: The system SHALL load workspace metadata and display agent status in a Rich `Table`, exiting with code `1` when status is `not_published` or `error`.\n1265: \n1266: ##### Scenario: Options and defaults\n1267: - **GIVEN** the user runs `status`\n1268: - **THEN** defaults SHALL be: `workspace` = `\".\"`; `provider` = `\"agentcube\"`; `verbose` = `False`\n1269: \n1270: ##### Scenario: Not published\n1271: - **GIVEN** metadata has no `agent_id`\n1272: - **WHEN** `get_status` returns `status == \"not_published\"`\n1273: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print guidance to publish first and exit with code `1`\n1274: \n1275: #### Requirement: Workspace validation (pack path)\n1276: The system SHALL validate that the workspace path exists and is a directory; for Python, require at least one `*.py` file; for Java, require `pom.xml`.\n1277: \n1278: ##### Scenario: Missing workspace\n1279: - **GIVEN** `workspace_path` does not exist\n1280: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_workspace_structure` runs\n1281: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with a message that the directory does not exist\n1282: \n1283: ##### Scenario: Python workspace without Python files\n1284: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language == \"python\"`\n1285: - **WHEN** no `*.py` exists in the workspace root\n1286: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")`\n1287: \n1288: #### Requirement: Metadata file format\n1289: The system SHALL persist agent configuration as YAML. The primary filename SHALL be `agent_metadata.yaml`; loading SHALL fall back to `agent.yaml` then `metadata.yaml` if the primary file is missing.\n1290: \n1291: ##### Scenario: Save location\n1292: - **GIVEN** metadata is saved\n1293: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.save_metadata` runs\n1294: - **THEN** the file SHALL be written to `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml` using `yaml.dump` with `default_flow_style=False`, `indent=2`, `sort_keys=False`, excluding `None` fields via `model_dump(exclude_none=True)`\n1295: \n1296: ##### Scenario: Schema validation\n1297: - **GIVEN** YAML is loaded\n1298: - **WHEN** fields violate `AgentMetadata` validators\n1299: - **THEN** Pydantic SHALL reject unsupported `language` / `build_mode` or invalid `port` range\n1300: \n1301: #### Requirement: Docker integration\n1302: The system SHALL use the Docker SDK (`docker.from_env()`) to build images, push to a registry when configured, and optionally remove images.\n1303: \n1304: ##### Scenario: Build image\n1305: - **GIVEN** Docker is running\n1306: - **WHEN** `DockerService.build_image` is called\n1307: - **THEN** it SHALL tag `{image_name}:{tag}`, pass optional `buildargs` from proxy settings, and return `image_name`, `image_id`, `image_size`, `build_time`\n1308: \n1309: ##### Scenario: Push image\n1310: - **GIVEN** a local image name and optional `registry_url` / credentials\n1311: - **WHEN** `DockerService.push_image` runs\n1312: - **THEN** it SHALL login if username and password are provided, retag when needed, stream push logs, and return `pushed_image` and `push_time`\n1313: \n1314: ##### Scenario: Remove image\n1315: - **GIVEN** `DockerService.remove_image(image_name)` is called\n1316: - **WHEN** removal succeeds\n1317: - **THEN** it SHALL return `True`; on failure it SHALL log a warning and return `False`\n1318: \n1319: #### Requirement: Kubernetes — standard provider\n1320: The system SHALL create or patch `Deployment` and `NodePort` `Service`, wait for rollout, report pod status, and support deletion.\n1321: \n1322: ##### Scenario: Deploy agent\n1323: - **GIVEN** `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent` is called\n1324: - **WHEN** resources are applied\n1325: - **THEN** the result SHALL include `deployment_name`, `service_name`, `namespace`, `replicas`, `container_port`, `node_port`, `service_url` as `http://localhost:{node_port}`\n1326: \n1327: ##### Scenario: Wait for ready\n1328: - **GIVEN** a deployment name\n1329: - **WHEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready` exceeds `timeout` seconds (default `120`)\n1330: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `TimeoutError`\n1331: \n1332: ##### Scenario: Delete agent\n1333: - **GIVEN** `delete_agent` is called\n1334: - **WHEN** deletion completes\n1335: - **THEN** it SHALL return `{\"status\": \"deleted\", \"deployment_name\", \"namespace\"}` ignoring 404 on individual deletes\n1336: \n1337: #### Requirement: Kubernetes — AgentCube AgentRuntime CR\n1338: The system SHALL create or patch an `AgentRuntime` custom object in group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, version `v1alpha1`, plural `agentruntimes`.\n1339: \n1340: ##### Scenario: Deploy CR\n1341: - **GIVEN** required readiness probe fields exist in metadata\n1342: - **WHEN** `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime` runs\n1343: - **THEN** it SHALL embed `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` / `ROUTER_URL` from parameters or environment when missing in `env_vars`, set `sessionTimeout` to `\"15m\"` and `maxSessionDuration` to `\"8h\"`, and reference `imagePullSecrets` `[{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}]`\n1344: \n1345: #### Requirement: AgentCube provider integration (CLI)\n1346: The system SHALL use `AgentCubeProvider` for `provider=agentcube` publish/status flows and `KubernetesProvider` for `provider=k8s`.\n1347: \n1348: ##### Scenario: Status for AgentRuntime\n1349: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `agentcube` and the CR exists\n1350: - **WHEN** `StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status` runs\n1351: - **THEN** status SHALL be read from `cr_object[\"status\"]` when present (`status`, `agentEndpoint`), else `created_no_status`, else `not_found_in_k8s`\n1352: \n1353: #### Requirement: Error handling patterns\n1354: The system SHALL use `_handle_error(e, command_name, verbose)` for subcommand exceptions: print `Error {command_name}: {e}` in red; if `verbose`, print traceback; raise `typer.Exit(1)`.\n1355: \n1356: ##### Scenario: Subcommand verbose vs global verbose\n1357: - **GIVEN** a subcommand's local `--verbose` is `True` but global `-v` was not passed\n1358: - **WHEN** an error occurs in that subcommand\n1359: - **THEN** traceback SHALL still be printed because `_handle_error` receives the subcommand's `verbose` flag\n1360: \n1361: ---\n1362: \n1363: ## 10. Client-Go Library\n1364: \n1365: Generated Kubernetes client code for API group **`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` / `v1alpha1`**, module path **`github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`**. Source reference: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`.\n1366: \n1367: ### Clientset\n1368: \n1369: #### `Interface` (`clientset/versioned/clientset.go`)\n1370: \n1371: ```go\n1372: type Interface interface {\n1373: \tDiscovery() discovery.DiscoveryInterface\n1374: \tRuntimeV1alpha1() runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n1375: }\n1376: ```\n1377: \n1378: #### `Clientset` struct\n1379: \n1380: Embeds `*discovery.DiscoveryClient` and holds `runtimeV1alpha1 *runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Client`.\n1381: \n1382: **Constructors**\n1383: \n1384: - `NewForConfig(c *rest.Config) (*Clientset, error)`\n1385: - `NewForConfigAndClient(c *rest.Config, httpClient *http.Client) (*Clientset, error)`\n1386: - `NewForConfigOrDie(c *rest.Config) *Clientset`\n1387: - `New(c rest.Interface) *Clientset`\n1388: \n1389: **Group accessor:** `RuntimeV1alpha1() runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface`\n1390: \n1391: ---\n1392: \n1393: ### Typed client — `runtime/v1alpha1`\n1394: \n1395: #### `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface` (`clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/runtime_client.go`)\n1396: \n1397: ```go\n1398: type RuntimeV1alpha1Interface interface {\n1399: \tRESTClient() rest.Interface\n1400: \tAgentRuntimesGetter\n1401: \tCodeInterpretersGetter\n1402: }\n1403: ```\n1404: \n1405: `RuntimeV1alpha1Client` implements this interface. REST defaults: `GroupVersion` = `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`.SchemeGroupVersion, `APIPath` = `/apis`, negotiated serializer from `clientset/versioned/scheme`.\n1406: \n1407: #### `AgentRuntimesGetter` / `AgentRuntimeInterface` (`.../agentruntime.go`)\n1408: \n1409: ```go\n1410: type AgentRuntimesGetter interface {\n1411: \tAgentRuntimes(namespace string) AgentRuntimeInterface\n1412: }\n1413: \n1414: type AgentRuntimeInterface interface {\n1415: \tCreate(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.CreateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n1416: \tUpdate(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n1417: \tUpdateStatus(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n1418: \tDelete(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.DeleteOptions) error\n1419: \tDeleteCollection(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.DeleteOptions, listOpts metav1.ListOptions) error\n1420: \tGet(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.GetOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n1421: \tList(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeList, error)\n1422: \tWatch(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (watch.Interface, error)\n1423: \tPatch(ctx context.Context, name string, pt types.PatchType, data []byte, opts metav1.PatchOptions, subresources ...string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n1424: \tAgentRuntimeExpansion\n1425: }\n1426: ```\n1427: \n1428: REST resource plural: **`agentruntimes`**.\n1429: \n1430: #### `CodeInterpretersGetter` / `CodeInterpreterInterface` (`.../codeinterpreter.go`)\n1431: \n1432: Same method shape as `AgentRuntimeInterface`, types `*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter` / `CodeInterpreterList`. REST resource plural: **`codeinterpreters`**.\n1433: \n1434: #### Expansion hooks (`generated_expansion.go`)\n1435: \n1436: ```go\n1437: type AgentRuntimeExpansion interface{}\n1438: type CodeInterpreterExpansion interface{}\n1439: ```\n1440: \n1441: (Empty — reserved for custom methods.)\n1442: \n1443: #### Fake clients (`typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/`)\n1444: \n1445: `fake_runtime_client.go`, `fake_agentruntime.go`, `fake_codeinterpreter.go` — test doubles implementing the typed interfaces; `doc.go` markers.\n1446: \n1447: ---\n1448: \n1449: ### Scheme (`clientset/versioned/scheme/`)\n1450: \n1451: | File | Role |\n1452: |------|------|\n1453: | `register.go` | Builds `Scheme`, `Codecs`, `ParameterCodec`; `AddToScheme` registers `runtime/v1alpha1` types |\n1454: | `doc.go` | Package doc |\n1455: \n1456: ---\n1457: \n1458: ### Informer factory\n1459: \n1460: #### `SharedInformerFactory` (`informers/externalversions/factory.go`)\n1461: \n1462: ```go\n1463: type SharedInformerFactory interface {\n1464: \tinternalinterfaces.SharedInformerFactory\n1465: \tStart(stopCh <-chan struct{})\n1466: \tShutdown()\n1467: \tWaitForCacheSync(stopCh <-chan struct{}) map[reflect.Type]bool\n1468: \tForResource(resource schema.GroupVersionResource) (GenericInformer, error)\n1469: \tInformerFor(obj runtime.Object, newFunc internalinterfaces.NewInformerFunc) cache.SharedIndexInformer\n1470: \tRuntime() externalversionsruntime.Interface\n1471: }\n1472: ```\n1473: \n1474: **Constructors / options**\n1475: \n1476: - `NewSharedInformerFactory(client versioned.Interface, defaultResync time.Duration)`\n1477: - `NewSharedInformerFactoryWithOptions(client, defaultResync, options ...SharedInformerOption)`\n1478: - `NewFilteredSharedInformerFactory` (deprecated alias to WithOptions)\n1479: - Options: `WithCustomResyncConfig`, `WithTweakListOptions`, `WithNamespace`, `WithTransform`\n1480: \n1481: ### Group interface (`informers/externalversions/runtime/interface.go`)\n1482: \n1483: ```go\n1484: type Interface interface {\n1485: \tV1alpha1() v1alpha1.Interface\n1486: }\n1487: ```\n1488: \n1489: `New(factory, namespace, tweakListOptions)` returns group accessor.\n1490: \n1491: ### Version interface (`informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/interface.go`)\n1492: \n1493: ```go\n1494: type Interface interface {\n1495: \tAgentRuntimes() AgentRuntimeInformer\n1496: \tCodeInterpreters() CodeInterpreterInformer\n1497: }\n1498: ```\n1499: \n1500: ### Per-type informers (`.../runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go`, `codeinterpreter.go`)\n1501: \n1502: Example (`AgentRuntimeInformer`):\n1503: \n1504: ```go\n1505: type AgentRuntimeInformer interface {\n1506: \tInformer() cache.SharedIndexInformer\n1507: \tLister() runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeLister\n1508: }\n1509: ```\n1510: \n1511: Also provides `NewAgentRuntimeInformer`, `NewFilteredAgentRuntimeInformer`, and analogous constructors for CodeInterpreter.\n1512: \n1513: ### Generic resource routing (`informers/externalversions/generic.go`)\n1514: \n1515: `ForResource` switches on:\n1516: \n1517: - `v1alpha1.SchemeGroupVersion.WithResource(\"agentruntimes\")` → `f.Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes().Informer()`\n1518: - `...WithResource(\"codeinterpreters\")` → `...CodeInterpreters().Informer()`\n1519: \n1520: ### `internalinterfaces` (`informers/externalversions/internalinterfaces/factory_interfaces.go`)\n1521: \n1522: ```go\n1523: type NewInformerFunc func(versioned.Interface, time.Duration) cache.SharedIndexInformer\n1524: type SharedInformerFactory interface {\n1525: \tStart(stopCh <-chan struct{})\n1526: \tInformerFor(obj runtime.Object, newFunc NewInformerFunc) cache.SharedIndexInformer\n1527: }\n1528: type TweakListOptionsFunc func(*metav1.ListOptions)\n1529: ```\n1530: \n1531: ---\n1532: \n1533: ### Listers (`listers/runtime/v1alpha1/`)\n1534: \n1535: #### `AgentRuntimeLister` / `AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister` (`agentruntime.go`)\n1536: \n1537: ```go\n1538: type AgentRuntimeLister interface {\n1539: \tList(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n1540: \tAgentRuntimes(namespace string) AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister\n1541: \tAgentRuntimeListerExpansion\n1542: }\n1543: \n1544: type AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister interface {\n1545: \tList(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n1546: \tGet(name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n1547: \tAgentRuntimeNamespaceListerExpansion\n1548: }\n1549: ```\n1550: \n1551: `NewAgentRuntimeLister` uses `runtimev1alpha1.Resource(\"agentruntime\").GroupResource()`.\n1552: \n1553: #### `CodeInterpreterLister` / `CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister` (`codeinterpreter.go`)\n1554: \n1555: Same pattern for `CodeInterpreter`; `NewCodeInterpreterLister` uses `Resource(\"codeinterpreter\").GroupResource()`.\n1556: \n1557: ### Expansion (`expansion_generated.go`)\n1558: \n1559: Empty expansion interfaces for listers and namespace listers (all four types).\n1560: \n1561: ---\n1562: \n1563: ### Fake clientset (`clientset/versioned/fake/`)\n1564: \n1565: | File | Role |\n1566: |------|------|\n1567: | `clientset_generated.go` | `NewSimpleClientset`, `NewClientset` — in-memory fake `Clientset` |\n1568: | `register.go` | Scheme registration for fakes |\n1569: | `doc.go` | Package doc |\n1570: \n1571: ---\n1572: \n1573: ### File index (all paths under `client-go/`)\n1574: \n1575: | Path | Role |\n1576: |------|------|\n1577: | `clientset/versioned/clientset.go` | `Clientset`, `Interface`, constructors |\n1578: | `clientset/versioned/scheme/register.go` | Scheme / codecs for generated client |\n1579: | `clientset/versioned/scheme/doc.go` | Doc |\n1580: | `clientset/versioned/fake/clientset_generated.go` | Fake clientset implementation |\n1581: | `clientset/versioned/fake/register.go` | Fake scheme wiring |\n1582: | `clientset/versioned/fake/doc.go` | Doc |\n1583: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/runtime_client.go` | `RuntimeV1alpha1Client`, `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface` |\n1584: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | `AgentRuntimeInterface`, typed REST client |\n1585: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | `CodeInterpreterInterface`, typed REST client |\n1586: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/generated_expansion.go` | Expansion interfaces |\n1587: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go` | Doc |\n1588: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_runtime_client.go` | Fake runtime group client |\n1589: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_agentruntime.go` | Fake AgentRuntime client |\n1590: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_codeinterpreter.go` | Fake CodeInterpreter client |\n1591: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/doc.go` | Doc |\n1592: | `informers/externalversions/factory.go` | `SharedInformerFactory`, options, `Start`/`Shutdown`/`WaitForCacheSync` |\n1593: | `informers/externalversions/generic.go` | `GenericInformer`, `ForResource` |\n1594: | `informers/externalversions/runtime/interface.go` | Group `runtime` informer accessor |\n1595: | `informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/interface.go` | `v1alpha1` informer accessors |\n1596: | `informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | AgentRuntime informer + constructor |\n1597: | `informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | CodeInterpreter informer + constructor |\n1598: | `informers/externalversions/internalinterfaces/factory_interfaces.go` | Small factory interface + `NewInformerFunc`, `TweakListOptionsFunc` |\n1599: | `listers/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | `AgentRuntimeLister`, namespace lister |\n1600: | `listers/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | `CodeInterpreterLister`, namespace lister |\n1601: | `listers/runtime/v1alpha1/expansion_generated.go` | Lister expansion interfaces |\n1602: \n1603: **Regeneration:** `make gen-client` → `hack/update-codegen.sh` (`k8s.io/code-generator` v0.34.1, `--with-watch`, output package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`).\n1604: \n1605: ---\n1606: \n1607: ## 11. Python SDK Design\n1608: \n1609: Source root: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/sdk-python/`.\n1610: \n1611: ### Package layout\n1612: \n1613: | Path | Role |\n1614: |------|------|\n1615: | `pyproject.toml` | Package `agentcube-sdk`, dependencies |\n1616: | `agentcube/__init__.py` | Public exports |\n1617: | `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | `CodeInterpreterClient` |\n1618: | `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | `AgentRuntimeClient` |\n1619: | `agentcube/exceptions.py` | Exception classes |\n1620: | `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` | Re-exports client classes |\n1621: | `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | `ControlPlaneClient` |\n1622: | `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` |\n1623: | `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` |\n1624: | `agentcube/utils/http.py` | `create_session` |\n1625: | `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | `read_token_from_file` |\n1626: | `agentcube/utils/log.py` | `get_logger` |\n1627: | `agentcube/utils/__init__.py` | Empty (module marker) |\n1628: | `examples/basic_usage.py`, `examples/agent_runtime_usage.py`, `scripts/e2e_picod_test.py`, `tests/*.py` | Non-library artifacts |\n1629: \n1630: ### Public exports (`agentcube/__init__.py`)\n1631: \n1632: ```python\n1633: from .code_interpreter import CodeInterpreterClient\n1634: from .agent_runtime import AgentRuntimeClient\n1635: \n1636: __all__ = [\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]\n1637: ```\n1638: \n1639: `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` additionally exports (not in root `__all__`):\n1640: \n1641: ```python\n1642: __all__ = [\n1643:     \"ControlPlaneClient\",\n1644:     \"CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\",\n1645:     \"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\",\n1646: ]\n1647: ```\n1648: \n1649: ### Configuration (no single `Configuration` class)\n1650: \n1651: There is **no** dedicated configuration dataclass. Defaults and environment resolution are distributed across:\n1652: \n1653: | Component | Resolved settings |\n1654: |-----------|-------------------|\n1655: | `ControlPlaneClient` | `base_url` ← `workload_manager_url` or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`; `Authorization` ← `auth_token` or SA token file; `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10` |\n1656: | `CodeInterpreterClient` | `router_url` ← arg or `ROUTER_URL` (required); `workload_manager_url` / `auth_token` passed to `ControlPlaneClient`; `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `verbose`, `session_id` |\n1657: | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`; `base_url` from `base_url` **or** `router_url`+`namespace`+`cr_name` |\n1658: | `AgentRuntimeClient` | `router_url` ← arg or `ROUTER_URL`; `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0` passed to data plane |\n1659: | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | same timeout defaults as above |\n1660: \n1661: ### `CodeInterpreterClient` (`agentcube/code_interpreter.py`)\n1662: \n1663: ```python\n1664: class CodeInterpreterClient:\n1665:     def __init__(\n1666:         self,\n1667:         name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n1668:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n1669:         ttl: int = 3600,\n1670:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n1671:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n1672:         auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n1673:         verbose: bool = False,\n1674:         session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n1675:     ): ...\n1676: \n1677:     def _init_data_plane(self) -> None: ...\n1678: \n1679:     def __enter__(self): ...\n1680:     def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None: ...\n1681: \n1682:     def stop(self) -> None: ...\n1683: \n1684:     def execute_command(self, command: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n1685:     def run_code(self, language: str, code: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n1686:     def write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n1687:     def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n1688:     def download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None: ...\n1689:     def list_files(self, path: str = \".\"): ...\n1690: ```\n1691: \n1692: **Fields set on instance:** `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `verbose`, `logger`, `cp_client`, `router_url`, `session_id`, `dp_client`.\n1693: \n1694: ### `AgentRuntimeClient` (`agentcube/agent_runtime.py`)\n1695: \n1696: ```python\n1697: class AgentRuntimeClient:\n1698:     def __init__(\n1699:         self,\n1700:         agent_name: str,\n1701:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n1702:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n1703:         verbose: bool = False,\n1704:         session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n1705:         timeout: int = 120,\n1706:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n1707:     ): ...\n1708: \n1709:     def __enter__(self): ...\n1710:     def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None: ...\n1711: \n1712:     def invoke(self, payload: Dict[str, Any], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> Any: ...\n1713: \n1714:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n1715: ```\n1716: \n1717: **Fields:** `agent_name`, `namespace`, `timeout`, `connect_timeout`, `logger`, `router_url`, `session_id`, `dp_client`.\n1718: \n1719: ### `ControlPlaneClient` (`agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`)\n1720: \n1721: ```python\n1722: class ControlPlaneClient:\n1723:     def __init__(\n1724:         self,\n1725:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n1726:         auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n1727:         timeout: int = 120,\n1728:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n1729:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n1730:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n1731:     ): ...\n1732: \n1733:     def create_session(\n1734:         self,\n1735:         name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n1736:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n1737:         metadata: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None,\n1738:         ttl: int = 3600,\n1739:     ) -> str: ...\n1740: \n1741:     def delete_session(self, session_id: str) -> bool: ...\n1742: \n1743:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n1744: ```\n1745: \n1746: #### Control plane — HTTP\n1747: \n1748: | Method | Path | Notes |\n1749: |--------|------|-------|\n1750: | `POST` | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` | JSON body: `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `metadata` |\n1751: | `DELETE` | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}` | 404 treated as success in `delete_session` |\n1752: \n1753: **Headers (default on `self.session`):**\n1754: \n1755: - `Content-Type`: `application/json`\n1756: - `Authorization`: `Bearer {token}` if token non-empty\n1757: \n1758: **Timeout:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)` on each request.\n1759: \n1760: ### `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` (`agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`)\n1761: \n1762: ```python\n1763: class CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient:\n1764:     def __init__(\n1765:         self,\n1766:         session_id: str,\n1767:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n1768:         namespace: Optional[str] = None,\n1769:         cr_name: Optional[str] = None,\n1770:         base_url: Optional[str] = None,\n1771:         timeout: int = 120,\n1772:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n1773:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n1774:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n1775:     ): ...\n1776: \n1777:     def _request(self, method: str, endpoint: str, body: Optional[bytes] = None, **kwargs) -> requests.Response: ...\n1778: \n1779:     def execute_command(self, command: Union[str, List[str]], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n1780:     def run_code(self, language: str, code: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n1781:     def write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n1782:     def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n1783:     def download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None: ...\n1784:     def list_files(self, path: str = \".\") -> Any: ...\n1785:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n1786: ```\n1787: \n1788: #### Data plane (Code Interpreter) — base URL\n1789: \n1790: If `base_url` is not provided:\n1791: \n1792: ```text\n1793: base_path = \"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\"\n1794: self.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n1795: ```\n1796: \n1797: #### Data plane — HTTP (relative to `self.base_url`)\n1798: \n1799: | Method | Relative path | Body / params |\n1800: |--------|---------------|---------------|\n1801: | `POST` | `api/execute` | JSON `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}` |\n1802: | `POST` | `api/files` | JSON `{\"path\", \"content\" (base64), \"mode\": \"0644\"}` |\n1803: | `POST` | `api/files` (multipart) | `files={'file': ...}`, `data={'path', 'mode'}` |\n1804: | `GET` | `api/files/{clean_path}` | `stream=True` for download (`clean_path = remote_path.lstrip(\"/\")`) |\n1805: | `GET` | `api/files` | query `path` |\n1806: \n1807: **Headers:**\n1808: \n1809: - Default session header: `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n1810: - JSON requests: `Content-Type: application/json` when `body` is set in `_request`\n1811: - Multipart upload: `x-agentcube-session-id` only (no JSON Content-Type on the outer request)\n1812: \n1813: **Note:** Docstring states Router handles JWT; SDK does not set `Authorization` on data plane.\n1814: \n1815: ### `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` (`agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`)\n1816: \n1817: ```python\n1818: class AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n1819:     SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n1820: \n1821:     def __init__(\n1822:         self,\n1823:         router_url: str,\n1824:         namespace: str,\n1825:         agent_name: str,\n1826:         timeout: int = 120,\n1827:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n1828:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n1829:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n1830:     ): ...\n1831: \n1832:     def bootstrap_session_id(self) -> str: ...\n1833: \n1834:     def invoke(\n1835:         self,\n1836:         session_id: str,\n1837:         payload: Dict[str, Any],\n1838:         timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n1839:     ) -> requests.Response: ...\n1840: \n1841:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n1842: ```\n1843: \n1844: #### Data plane (Agent Runtime) — base URL\n1845: \n1846: ```text\n1847: base_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\n1848: self.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n1849: ```\n1850: \n1851: #### Data plane — HTTP\n1852: \n1853: | Method | URL | Headers | Body |\n1854: |--------|-----|---------|------|\n1855: | `GET` | `self.base_url` | (session default headers only) | — |\n1856: | `POST` | `self.base_url` | `x-agentcube-session-id`, `Content-Type: application/json` | `json=payload` |\n1857: \n1858: **Timeouts:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)` where `timeout` for `invoke` read side is the method argument or `self.timeout`.\n1859: \n1860: ### `create_session` (`agentcube/utils/http.py`)\n1861: \n1862: ```python\n1863: def create_session(\n1864:     pool_connections: int = 10,\n1865:     pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n1866: ) -> requests.Session: ...\n1867: ```\n1868: \n1869: Mounts `HTTPAdapter` for `http://` and `https://`.\n1870: \n1871: ### `read_token_from_file` (`agentcube/utils/utils.py`)\n1872: \n1873: ```python\n1874: def read_token_from_file(file_path: str) -> str: ...\n1875: ```\n1876: \n1877: Returns file contents stripped, or `\"\"` on `FileNotFoundError`.\n1878: \n1879: ### `get_logger` (`agentcube/utils/log.py`)\n1880: \n1881: ```python\n1882: def get_logger(name: str, level: Union[int, str] = logging.INFO) -> logging.Logger: ...\n1883: ```\n1884: \n1885: ### Exception hierarchy (`agentcube/exceptions.py`)\n1886: \n1887: ```python\n1888: class AgentCubeError(Exception):\n1889:     \"\"\"Base exception for AgentCube SDK\"\"\"\n1890:     pass\n1891: \n1892: class CommandExecutionError(AgentCubeError):\n1893:     \"\"\"Raised when command execution returns non-zero exit code\"\"\"\n1894:     def __init__(self, exit_code, stderr, command=None):\n1895:         self.exit_code = exit_code\n1896:         self.stderr = stderr\n1897:         self.command = command\n1898:         super().__init__(f\"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\")\n1899: \n1900: class SessionError(AgentCubeError):\n1901:     \"\"\"Raised when session creation or management fails\"\"\"\n1902:     pass\n1903: \n1904: class DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError):\n1905:     \"\"\"Raised when Data Plane operations fail\"\"\"\n1906:     pass\n1907: ```\n1908: \n1909: ### Dependencies (`sdk-python/pyproject.toml`)\n1910: \n1911: ```toml\n1912: dependencies = [\n1913:     \"requests\",\n1914:     \"PyJWT>=2.0.0\",\n1915:     \"cryptography\",\n1916: ]\n1917: ```\n1918: \n1919: - `requires-python = \">=3.10\"`\n1920: - Build: `setuptools>=61.0`, `wheel`; backend `setuptools.build_meta`\n1921: - Packages: `where = [\".\"]`, `include = [\"agentcube*\"]`, `namespaces = false`\n1922: \n1923: ---\n1924: \n1925: ## 12. Python SDK Specification\n1926: \n1927: ### Purpose\n1928: \n1929: Python client library (`agentcube-sdk`) for creating Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and executing code/files via the Router (data plane), plus invoking AgentRuntime workloads through the Router.\n1930: \n1931: ### Requirements\n1932: \n1933: #### Requirement: `CodeInterpreterClient` lifecycle\n1934: The system SHALL construct a client that either reuses `session_id` or creates a session via `ControlPlaneClient.create_session`, then initializes `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with header `x-agentcube-session-id`.\n1935: \n1936: ##### Scenario: Context manager cleanup\n1937: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is used as a context manager\n1938: - **WHEN** the block exits (with or without exception)\n1939: - **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()`, which closes the data-plane session, deletes the control-plane session if `session_id` was set, and closes the control plane HTTP session\n1940: \n1941: ##### Scenario: Data plane init failure after session create\n1942: - **GIVEN** `session_id` was not provided and `create_session` succeeded\n1943: - **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` raises\n1944: - **THEN** the client SHALL log a warning, call `delete_session(session_id)`, set `session_id` to `None`, and re-raise\n1945: \n1946: ##### Scenario: Router URL required\n1947: - **GIVEN** neither `router_url` nor environment variable `ROUTER_URL` is set\n1948: - **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__` runs\n1949: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` explaining that Router URL must be provided via argument or `ROUTER_URL`\n1950: \n1951: #### Requirement: Code Interpreter — execute, files, stop\n1952: The system SHALL expose `execute_command`, `run_code`, `write_file`, `upload_file`, `download_file`, `list_files`, and `stop` delegating to the data plane client where applicable.\n1953: \n1954: ##### Scenario: Command non-zero exit\n1955: - **GIVEN** `execute_command` receives a response with `exit_code != 0`\n1956: - **WHEN** the response JSON is parsed\n1957: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` with `exit_code`, `stderr`, and `command`\n1958: \n1959: ##### Scenario: Python code execution path\n1960: - **GIVEN** `language` is `python`, `py`, or `python3`\n1961: - **WHEN** `run_code` runs\n1962: - **THEN** the system SHALL write a timestamped `.py` file via `write_file` and execute `python3 <file>` through `execute_command`\n1963: \n1964: #### Requirement: `AgentRuntimeClient` lifecycle\n1965: The system SHALL bootstrap or reuse `session_id` from the Agent Runtime invocation endpoint via `GET` on the base invocation URL, then `POST` JSON payloads with session header.\n1966: \n1967: ##### Scenario: Context manager\n1968: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is used as a context manager\n1969: - **WHEN** the block exits\n1970: - **THEN** `close()` SHALL close the underlying `requests.Session`\n1971: \n1972: ##### Scenario: Bootstrap session id\n1973: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is not provided\n1974: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n1975: - **THEN** it SHALL `GET` `{router}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/` and read header `x-agentcube-session-id`; if missing, raise `ValueError` with message `Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id`\n1976: \n1977: ##### Scenario: Invoke without session\n1978: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is falsy\n1979: - **WHEN** `invoke` is called\n1980: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n1981: \n1982: #### Requirement: HTTP client contracts — control plane\n1983: The system SHALL use `requests.Session` with connection pooling (`HTTPAdapter`) for Workload Manager calls.\n1984: \n1985: ##### Scenario: Create session\n1986: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient.create_session(name, namespace, metadata=None, ttl=3600)`\n1987: - **WHEN** the request succeeds\n1988: - **THEN** the client SHALL `POST {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` with JSON body `{\"name\",\"namespace\",\"ttl\",\"metadata\"}` and return `data[\"sessionId\"]` or raise `ValueError` if absent\n1989: \n1990: ##### Scenario: Delete session\n1991: - **GIVEN** `delete_session(session_id)`\n1992: - **WHEN** the server returns 404\n1993: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`; on other failures it SHALL log and return `False`\n1994: \n1995: ##### Scenario: Workload Manager URL and auth\n1996: - **GIVEN** `workload_manager_url` and `auth_token` may be omitted\n1997: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n1998: - **THEN** `base_url` SHALL resolve from `workload_manager_url` or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`; token SHALL resolve from `auth_token` or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` via `read_token_from_file`, and if present set `Authorization: Bearer {token}`\n1999: \n2000: #### Requirement: HTTP client contracts — data plane (Code Interpreter)\n2001: The system SHALL target Router-relative paths under `{base_url}` derived from `urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/{ns}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\")` unless `base_url` is passed explicitly.\n2002: \n2003: ##### Scenario: Execute command\n2004: - **WHEN** `execute_command` posts to `api/execute`\n2005: - **THEN** the body SHALL be JSON `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}` and read timeout SHALL be `timeout_value + 2.0` seconds when numeric (to avoid `ReadTimeout` before PicoD returns exit 124)\n2006: \n2007: ##### Scenario: Files API\n2008: - **WHEN** `write_file` runs\n2009: - **THEN** it SHALL `POST api/files` with base64 `content`, `path`, `mode` `\"0644\"`\n2010: - **WHEN** `upload_file` runs\n2011: - **THEN** it SHALL `POST` multipart to `api/files` with headers including `x-agentcube-session-id`\n2012: \n2013: #### Requirement: HTTP client contracts — data plane (Agent Runtime)\n2014: The system SHALL `POST` JSON to the invocation base URL with headers `x-agentcube-session-id` and `Content-Type: application/json`.\n2015: \n2016: ##### Scenario: Invoke timeout tuple\n2017: - **GIVEN** `invoke(..., timeout=None)`\n2018: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n2019: - **THEN** `timeout` SHALL be `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` where `self.timeout` defaults to `120`\n2020: \n2021: #### Requirement: Session header management\n2022: The system SHALL use lowercase header name `x-agentcube-session-id` for SDK Router requests (`CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` default session header; `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` uses class constant `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"`).\n2023: \n2024: ##### Scenario: Code Interpreter session header\n2025: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is constructed\n2026: - **WHEN** any `_request` or upload runs\n2027: - **THEN** the session SHALL include `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` (upload sets it explicitly on the multipart POST)\n2028: \n2029: #### Requirement: Exception hierarchy\n2030: The system SHALL define `AgentCubeError`, `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, and `DataPlaneError` in `agentcube.exceptions`.\n2031: \n2032: ##### Scenario: Command failure\n2033: - **GIVEN** remote command returns non-zero exit code in JSON\n2034: - **WHEN** `execute_command` processes the response\n2035: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` (subclass of `AgentCubeError`)\n2036: \n2037: ##### Scenario: SessionError / DataPlaneError usage\n2038: - **GIVEN** the current package sources under `agentcube/`\n2039: - **WHEN** searching for `raise SessionError` / `raise DataPlaneError`\n2040: - **THEN** these classes are defined for extension but not raised by the core client modules in the extracted tree (callers MAY rely on `ValueError`, `requests` exceptions, or `CommandExecutionError`)\n2041: \n2042: #### Requirement: Timeout behavior\n2043: The system SHALL default control-plane and data-plane read timeouts to `120` seconds and connect timeout to `5.0` seconds unless overridden per call.\n2044: \n2045: ##### Scenario: Per-call override for code execution\n2046: - **GIVEN** `execute_command(command, timeout=None)`\n2047: - **WHEN** `timeout` is `None`\n2048: - **THEN** the effective timeout value SHALL default to `self.timeout` (`120`) for constructing the PicoD timeout string and read-timeout buffer logic\n2049: \n2050: ##### Scenario: AgentRuntimeClient constructor timeouts\n2051: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient(..., timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0)`\n2052: - **WHEN** `invoke` is called without `timeout`\n2053: - **THEN** read timeout SHALL be `120` (instance default)\n2054: \n2055: ---\n2056: \n2057: **Public package surface:** `agentcube/__init__.py` exports only `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient` in `__all__`.\n2058: \n2059: ---\n2060: \n2061: # AR-024 — DockerService 封装\n2062: \n2063: - **AR ID**: AR-024\n2064: - **Module**: cmd/cli\n2065: - **Language**: Python\n2066: - **Size**: M\n2067: - **Status**: ST-1 Completed (design.md)\n2068: \n2069: ## 1. Architecture\n2070: \n2071: ### 1.1 Overview\n2072: \n2073: DockerService provides a high-level abstraction over the Docker Python SDK (`docker` package) for building, pushing, and managing container images within the AgentCube CLI. It encapsulates common Docker operations with consistent error handling, logging, and result formatting.\n2074: \n2075: ### 1.2 Class Diagram\n2076: \n2077: ```\n2078: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n2079: │                            DockerService                                      │\n2080: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n2081: │ - _client: docker.DockerClient                                               │\n2082: │ - _verbose: bool                                                            │\n2083: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n2084: │ + __init__(verbose: bool = False)                                           │\n2085: │ + check_docker_available() -> bool                                         │\n2086: │ + build_image(...) -> Dict[str, str]                                        │\n2087: │ + get_image_info(image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]                         │\n2088: │ + push_image(...) -> Dict[str, str]                                         │\n2089: │ + remove_image(image_name: str) -> bool                                     │\n2090: │ - _get_image_info(image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]                       │\n2091: │ - _format_size(size_bytes: int) -> str                                      │\n2092: │ - _docker_login_sdk(registry: Optional[str], username: str, password: str) │\n2093: │ - _tag_image_sdk(source_image: str, target_image: str)                    │\n2094: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n2095: ```\n2096: \n2097: ## 2. Data Structures\n2098: \n2099: ### 2.1 Method Signatures\n2100: \n2101: ```python\n2102: class DockerService:\n2103:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n2104:         \"\"\"Initialize DockerService with optional verbose logging.\"\"\"\n2105:         self._verbose = verbose\n2106:         self._client = None\n2107: \n2108:     def check_docker_available(self) -> bool:\n2109:         \"\"\"Check if Docker is available and running.\n2110:         \n2111:         Returns:\n2112:             bool: True if Docker is available, False otherwise.\n2113:         \"\"\"\n2114: \n2115:     def build_image(\n2116:         self,\n2117:         dockerfile_path: Path,\n2118:         context_path: Path,\n2119:         image_name: str,\n2120:         tag: str = \"latest\",\n2121:         build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n2122:     ) -> Dict[str, str]:\n2123:         \"\"\"Build a Docker image from a Dockerfile.\n2124:         \n2125:         Args:\n2126:             dockerfile_path: Path to the Dockerfile.\n2127:             context_path: Build context directory.\n2128:             image_name: Name of the image to build.\n2129:             tag: Image tag (default: \"latest\").\n2130:             build_args: Optional build arguments for Dockerfile.\n2131:         \n2132:         Returns:\n2133:             Dict containing:\n2134:                 - image_name: Full image name with tag\n2135:                 - image_id: Docker image ID\n2136:                 - image_size: Human-readable size\n2137:                 - build_time: Build timestamp\n2138:         \"\"\"\n2139: \n2140:     def get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]:\n2141:         \"\"\"Get information about a local Docker image.\n2142:         \n2143:         Args:\n2144:             image_name: Name or ID of the image.\n2145:         \n2146:         Returns:\n2147:             Dict containing image details.\n2148:         \"\"\"\n2149: \n2150:     def push_image(\n2151:         self,\n2152:         image_name: str,\n2153:         registry_url: Optional[str] = None,\n2154:         username: Optional[str] = None,\n2155:         password: Optional[str] = None,\n2156:     ) -> Dict[str, str]:\n2157:         \"\"\"Push a Docker image to a registry.\n2158:         \n2159:         Args:\n2160:             image_name: Name of the image to push.\n2161:             registry_url: Optional registry URL.\n2162:             username: Optional registry username.\n2163:             password: Optional registry password.\n2164:         \n2165:         Returns:\n2166:             Dict containing:\n2167:                 - pushed_image: Full pushed image name\n2168:                 - push_time: Push timestamp\n2169:         \"\"\"\n2170: \n2171:     def remove_image(self, image_name: str) -> bool:\n2172:         \"\"\"Remove a local Docker image.\n2173:         \n2174:         Args:\n2175:             image_name: Name or ID of the image to remove.\n2176:         \n2177:         Returns:\n2178:             bool: True if removal succeeded, False on failure.\n2179:         \"\"\"\n2180: ```\n2181: \n2182: ### 2.2 Return Type Specifications\n2183: \n2184: #### build_image Return Value\n2185: \n2186: | Field | Type | Description |\n2187: |-------|------|-------------|\n2188: | `image_name` | `str` | Full image name with tag (e.g., `my-agent:v1.0.0`) |\n2189: | `image_id` | `str` | Docker image ID (e.g., `sha256:abc123...`) |\n2190: | `image_size` | `str` | Human-readable size (e.g., `1.2 GB`) |\n2191: | `build_time` | `str` | ISO 8601 timestamp of build completion |\n2192: \n2193: #### get_image_info Return Value\n2194: \n2195: | Field | Type | Description |\n2196: |-------|------|-------------|\n2197: | `image_name` | `str` | Image name |\n2198: | `image_id` | `str` | Image ID |\n2199: | `tags` | `List[str]` | Image tags |\n2200: | `size` | `str` | Human-readable size |\n2201: | `created` | `str` | Creation timestamp |\n2202: \n2203: #### push_image Return Value\n2204: \n2205: | Field | Type | Description |\n2206: |-------|------|-------------|\n2207: | `pushed_image` | `str` | Full pushed image URL |\n2208: | `push_time` | `str` | ISO 8601 timestamp |\n2209: \n2210: ## 3. API Contracts\n2211: \n2212: ### 3.1 Docker SDK Integration\n2213: \n2214: The service uses the `docker` Python package (version >= 6.0.0):\n2215: \n2216: ```python\n2217: import docker\n2218: from docker import DockerClient\n2219: from docker.models.images import Image\n2220: \n2221: # Initialize client\n2222: self._client = docker.from_env()\n2223: \n2224: # Build image\n2225: image: Image = self._client.images.build(\n2226:     path=str(context_path),\n2227:     dockerfile=str(dockerfile_path),\n2228:     tag=f\"{image_name}:{tag}\",\n2229:     buildargs=build_args or {},\n2230:     rm=True,\n2231: )\n2232: \n2233: # Push image\n2234: image.push()\n2235: \n2236: # Remove image\n2237: self._client.images.remove(image_name)\n2238: ```\n2239: \n2240: ### 3.2 Error Handling\n2241: \n2242: | Error Type | Scenario | Handling |\n2243: |------------|----------|-----------|\n2244: | `docker.errors.DockerException` | Docker not available | Return `False` from `check_docker_available()` |\n2245: | `docker.errors.BuildError` | Build failure | Raise `RuntimeError` with details |\n2246: | `docker.errors.APIError` | API error | Log and re-raise |\n2247: | `ImageNotFound` | Image not found | Return empty dict from `get_image_info()` |\n2248: \n2249: ### 3.3 Logging\n2250: \n2251: When `verbose=True`:\n2252: \n2253: - Log Docker API calls at DEBUG level\n2254: - Log image build progress\n2255: - Log push/pull progress streams\n2256: - Log Docker daemon responses\n2257: \n2258: ```python\n2259: import logging\n2260: \n2261: def _log(self, message: str) -> None:\n2262:     if self._verbose:\n2263:         logging.debug(f\"[DockerService] {message}\")\n2264: ```\n2265: \n2266: ## 4. Implementation Details\n2267: \n2268: ### 4.1 Lazy Client Initialization\n2269: \n2270: ```python\n2271: def _get_client(self) -> DockerClient:\n2272:     \"\"\"Lazily initialize Docker client.\"\"\"\n2273:     if self._client is None:\n2274:         self._client = docker.from_env()\n2275:     return self._client\n2276: ```\n2277: \n2278: ### 4.2 Image Info Retrieval\n2279: \n2280: ```python\n2281: def _get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]:\n2282:     \"\"\"Internal method to retrieve image details.\"\"\"\n2283:     try:\n2284:         image = self._client.images.get(image_name)\n2285:         return {\n2286:             \"image_name\": image.tags[0] if image.tags else image_name,\n2287:             \"image_id\": image.id,\n2288:             \"tags\": image.tags,\n2289:             \"size\": self._format_size(image.attrs[\"Size\"]),\n2290:             \"created\": image.attrs[\"Created\"],\n2291:         }\n2292:     except docker.errors.ImageNotFound:\n2293:         return {}\n2294: ```\n2295: \n2296: ### 4.3 Size Formatting\n2297: \n2298: ```python\n2299: def _format_size(self, size_bytes: int) -> str:\n2300:     \"\"\"Format byte size to human-readable string.\"\"\"\n2301:     for unit in [\"B\", \"KB\", \"MB\", \"GB\", \"TB\"]:\n2302:         if size_bytes < 1024.0:\n2303:             return f\"{size_bytes:.2f} {unit}\"\n2304:         size_bytes /= 1024.0\n2305:     return f\"{size_bytes:.2f} PB\"\n2306: ```\n2307: \n2308: ### 4.4 Registry Login\n2309: \n2310: ```python\n2311: def _docker_login_sdk(\n2312:     self,\n2313:     registry: Optional[str],\n2314:     username: str,\n2315:     password: str,\n2316: ) -> None:\n2317:     \"\"\"Login to Docker registry.\"\"\"\n2318:     if registry:\n2319:         self._client.login(registry=registry, username=username, password=password)\n2320:     else:\n2321:         self._client.login(username=username, password=password)\n2322: ```\n2323: \n2324: ### 4.5 Image Tagging\n2325: \n2326: ```python\n2327: def _tag_image_sdk(self, source_image: str, target_image: str) -> None:\n2328:     \"\"\"Tag a Docker image.\"\"\"\n2329:     image = self._client.images.get(source_image)\n2330:     image.tag(target_image)\n2331: ```\n2332: \n2333: ## 5. Testing Strategy\n2334: \n2335: ### 5.1 Unit Tests\n2336: \n2337: - Test `check_docker_available()` with mocked Docker client\n2338: - Test `build_image()` with mocked build response\n2339: - Test `get_image_info()` with mocked image data\n2340: - Test `push_image()` with mocked push response\n2341: - Test `remove_image()` success and failure cases\n2342: - Test `_format_size()` edge cases\n2343: - Test `_get_image_info()` with non-existent image\n2344: \n2345: ### 5.2 Integration Tests\n2346: \n2347: Requires Docker daemon running:\n2348: \n2349: ```python\n2350: import pytest\n2351: \n2352: @pytest.fixture\n2353: def docker_service():\n2354:     return DockerService(verbose=True)\n2355: \n2356: def test_docker_available(docker_service):\n2357:     assert docker_service.check_docker_available() is True\n2358: \n2359: def test_build_image(docker_service, tmp_path):\n2360:     # Create minimal Dockerfile\n2361:     dockerfile = tmp_path / \"Dockerfile\"\n2362:     dockerfile.write_text(\"FROM alpine:latest\\n\")\n2363:     \n2364:     result = docker_service.build_image(\n2365:         dockerfile_path=dockerfile,\n2366:         context_path=tmp_path,\n2367:         image_name=\"test-image\",\n2368:         tag=\"latest\",\n2369:     )\n2370:     \n2371:     assert \"image_id\" in result\n2372:     assert result[\"image_name\"] == \"test-image:latest\"\n2373: ```\n2374: \n2375: ### 5.3 Mock Objects\n2376: \n2377: ```python\n2378: from unittest.mock import MagicMock, patch\n2379: \n2380: @pytest.fixture\n2381: def mock_docker_client():\n2382:     with patch(\"docker.from_env\") as mock:\n2383:         client = MagicMock()\n2384:         mock.return_value = client\n2385:         yield client\n2386: ```\n2387: \n2388: ## 6. Dependencies\n2389: \n2390: ### 6.1 Required Dependencies\n2391: \n2392: ```toml\n2393: dependencies = [\n2394:     \"docker>=6.0.0\",\n2395: ]\n2396: ```\n2397: \n2398: ### 6.2 Dev Dependencies\n2399: \n2400: ```toml\n2401: [project.optional-dependencies]\n2402: test = [\n2403:     \"pytest>=7.4.0\",\n2404:     \"pytest-mock>=3.11.0\",\n2405: ]\n2406: ```\n2407: \n2408: ## 7. Usage Examples\n2409: \n2410: ### 7.1 Basic Image Build\n2411: \n2412: ```python\n2413: from pathlib import Path\n2414: from agentcube.services.docker_service import DockerService\n2415: \n2416: docker_svc = DockerService(verbose=True)\n2417: \n2418: result = docker_svc.build_image(\n2419:     dockerfile_path=Path(\"./Dockerfile\"),\n2420:     context_path=Path(\"./workspace\"),\n2421:     image_name=\"my-agent\",\n2422:     tag=\"v1.0.0\",\n2423: )\n2424: \n2425: print(f\"Built: {result['image_id']} ({result['image_size']})\")\n2426: ```\n2427: \n2428: ### 7.2 Push to Registry\n2429: \n2430: ```python\n2431: result = docker_svc.push_image(\n2432:     image_name=\"my-agent:v1.0.0\",\n2433:     registry_url=\"registry.example.com\",\n2434:     username=\"user\",\n2435:     password=\"pass\",\n2436: )\n2437: \n2438: print(f\"Pushed to: {result['pushed_image']}\")\n2439: ```\n2440: \n2441: ### 7.3 Check Docker Availability\n2442: \n2443: ```python\n2444: if not docker_svc.check_docker_available():\n2445:     print(\"Docker is not available\")\n2446:     sys.exit(1)\n2447: ```\n2448: \n2449: ---\n2450: \n2451: *Note: The implementation uses `agent_metadata.yaml` as the canonical metadata filename (with `agent.yaml` / `metadata.yaml` fallbacks for load). Documentation that refers to `agentcube.yaml` SHALL be treated as naming drift unless a separate file is introduced in code.*\n2452: ```\n\n(End of file - total 2452 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"- **WHEN** the user passes `--version` (eager option, `Optional[bool]`, default `None`)\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print `AgentCube CLI (kubectl agentcube) version: {__version__}` (Rich markup) and exit without running a subcommand (`typer.Exit()`), where `__version__` is `0.1.0` from `agentcube.__init__`\n\n##### Scenario: Global verbose logging\n- **GIVEN** the user passes `--verbose` / `-v` (`bool`, default `False`) on the root callback\n- **WHEN** the callback runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)`\n\n#### Requirement: `pack` command\nThe system SHALL provide `pack` to validate and prepare a workspace, merge CLI overrides into metadata, optionally generate a `Dockerfile`, and report paths.\n\n##### Scenario: Options and defaults\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `pack`\n- **WHEN** options are omitted\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL use: `workspace` = `\".\"` (`-f` / `--workspace`, `str`); `agent_name` = `None` (`--agent-name`, `Optional[str]`); `language` = `None` (`--language`); `entrypoint` = `None` (`--entrypoint`); `port` = `None` (`--port`, `Optional[int]`); `build_mode` = `None` (`--build-mode`); `description` = `None` (`--description`); `output` = `None` (`--output`); `verbose` = `False` (`--verbose`, command-local)\n\n##### Scenario: Successful pack\n- **GIVEN** a valid workspace path\n- **WHEN** `pack` completes without exception\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print success with `agent_name`, resolved `workspace_path`, and `metadata_path` (reported as `{final_workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml`), using a Rich `Progress` spinner during work","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775866000742,"end":1775866000761}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775866000791,"sessionID":"ses_28623daf0ffez95ulaFqw2gZJI","part":{"id":"prt_d79dcb57d0012guCtxUQUgNoVF","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d79dc95560011QF1YDgNqqDzH0","sessionID":"ses_28623daf0ffez95ulaFqw2gZJI","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":49046,"input":13720,"output":320,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":35006}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775866008166,"sessionID":"ses_28623daf0ffez95ulaFqw2gZJI","part":{"id":"prt_d79dcd2640019BPz36sgrv6JQT","messageID":"msg_d79dcb5ad001doOJkcEzFWv2v8","sessionID":"ses_28623daf0ffez95ulaFqw2gZJI","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775866057925,"sessionID":"ses_28623daf0ffez95ulaFqw2gZJI","part":{"id":"prt_d79dcdd69001nGScP3nw4Zik2W","messageID":"msg_d79dcb5ad001doOJkcEzFWv2v8","sessionID":"ses_28623daf0ffez95ulaFqw2gZJI","type":"tool","tool":"edit","callID":"toolu_cc6a6dbc71094540b678d60d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md","newString":"---\n\n# AR-025 — MetadataService 与数据模型\n\n- **AR ID**: AR-025\n- **Module**: cmd/cli\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n- **Status**: ST-1 Completed (design.md)\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Overview\n\nMetadataService provides centralized management of agent metadata throughout the CLI lifecycle. It handles loading, validation, saving, and updating of `AgentMetadata` configuration files that track agent state from packaging through deployment.\n\n### 1.2 Package Structure\n\n```\nagentcube/\n├── models/\n│   └── pack_models.py          # MetadataOptions dataclass\n├── services/\n│   └── metadata_service.py      # AgentMetadata, MetadataService\n└── runtime/\n    └── pack_runtime.py         # Uses MetadataService\n```\n\n## 2. Data Models\n\n### 2.1 AgentMetadata (Pydantic BaseModel)\n\nThe core data model representing agent configuration and state.\n\n```python\nfrom pydantic import BaseModel, Field, field_validator\nfrom typing import Optional, Dict, Any\n\nclass AgentMetadata(BaseModel):\n    agent_name: str = Field(..., description=\"Unique name identifying the agent\")\n    description: Optional[str] = None\n    language: str = \"python\"\n    entrypoint: str = Field(..., description=\"Command to launch the agent\")\n    port: int = 8080\n    build_mode: str = \"local\"\n    region: Optional[str] = None\n    version: Optional[str] = None\n    image: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None\n    auth: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None\n    requirements_file: Optional[str] = \"requirements.txt\"\n    registry_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    registry_username: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    registry_password: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = None\n    workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None\n    router_url: Optional[str] = None\n    readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = None\n    readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = None\n    agent_id: Optional[str] = None\n    session_id: Optional[str] = None\n    k8s_deployment: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None\n\n    @field_validator('language')\n    @classmethod\n    def validate_language(cls, v: str) -> str:\n        valid = ['python', 'java']\n        if v.lower() not in valid:\n            raise ValueError(f\"language must be one of {valid}\")\n        return v.lower()\n\n    @field_validator('build_mode')\n    @classmethod\n    def validate_build_mode(cls, v: str) -> str:\n        valid = ['local', 'cloud']\n        if v.lower() not in valid:\n            raise ValueError(f\"build_mode must be one of {valid}\")\n        return v.lower()\n\n    @field_validator('port')\n    @classmethod\n    def validate_port(cls, v: int) -> int:\n        if not 1 <= v <= 65535:\n            raise ValueError(\"port must be between 1 and 65535\")\n        return v\n```\n\n### 2.2 MetadataOptions (dataclass)\n\nCLI options wrapper for passing parameters to runtime classes.\n\n```python\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass, field\nfrom typing import Optional, Dict, Any\n\n@dataclass\nclass MetadataOptions:\n    agent_name: Optional[str] = None\n    language: Optional[str] = 'python'\n    entrypoint: Optional[str] = None\n    port: Optional[int] = 8080\n    build_mode: Optional[str] = 'local'\n    requirements_file: Optional[str] = None\n    description: Optional[str] = None\n    workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    router_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = 8080\n    registry_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    registry_username: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    registry_password: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = \"\"\n\n    @classmethod\n    def from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> \"MetadataOptions\":\n        \"\"\"Convert CLI options dict to MetadataOptions.\"\"\"\n        return cls(**{k: v for k, v in options.items() if k in cls.__annotations__})\n```\n\n## 3. MetadataService Implementation\n\n### 3.1 Class Definition\n\n```python\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Dict, Any, Optional\nimport yaml\nimport logging\n\nclass MetadataService:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n        self._verbose = verbose\n        self._logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n\n    def load_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> AgentMetadata:\n        \"\"\"Load metadata from workspace.\n        \n        Priority: agent_metadata.yaml > agent.yaml > metadata.yaml\n        \"\"\"\n\n    def save_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Save metadata to agent_metadata.yaml.\"\"\"\n\n    def update_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, updates: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata:\n        \"\"\"Update specific fields in metadata.\"\"\"\n\n    def validate_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"Validate workspace structure.\"\"\"\n\n    def _validate_python_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Validate Python-specific workspace requirements.\"\"\"\n\n    def _validate_java_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Validate Java-specific workspace requirements.\"\"\"\n```\n\n### 3.2 File Format Specification\n\n**Primary filename:** `agent_metadata.yaml`\n\n**Fallbacks (load only):**\n1. `agent_metadata.yaml`\n2. `agent.yaml`\n3. `metadata.yaml`\n\n**YAML serialization:**\n\n```python\ndef save_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n    metadata_file = workspace_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n    with open(metadata_file, 'w') as f:\n        yaml.dump(\n            metadata.model_dump(exclude_none=True),\n            f,\n            default_flow_style=False,\n            indent=2,\n            sort_keys=False,\n        )\n```\n\n### 3.3 Load Fallback Logic\n\n```python\ndef load_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> AgentMetadata:\n    for filename in ['agent_metadata.yaml', 'agent.yaml', 'metadata.yaml']:\n        metadata_file = workspace_path / filename\n        if metadata_file.exists():\n            with open(metadata_file) as f:\n                data = yaml.safe_load(f)\n            return AgentMetadata(**data)\n    \n    # Return default if no file found\n    return AgentMetadata(\n        agent_name=workspace_path.name,\n        language=\"python\",\n        entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n    )\n```\n\n## 4. CLI Integration\n\n### 4.1 Pack Command Flow\n\n```\npack command\n    │\n    ▼\nPackRuntime.pack()\n    │\n    ├─ _validate_workspace_structure()\n    │     └─ MetadataService.validate_workspace()\n    │\n    ├─ _load_or_create_metadata()\n    │     └─ MetadataService.load_metadata()\n    │\n    ├─ _apply_option_overrides()\n    │     └─ CLI options override metadata fields\n    │\n    └─ _update_pack_metadata()\n          └─ MetadataService.save_metadata()\n```\n\n### 4.2 Build Command Flow\n\n```\nbuild command\n    │\n    ▼\nBuildRuntime.build()\n    │\n    ├─ _increment_version()\n    │     └─ Update metadata.version\n    │\n    ├─ _build_local()\n    │     └─ DockerService.build_image()\n    │\n    └─ _update_build_metadata()\n          └─ MetadataService.update_metadata()\n```\n\n### 4.3 Publish Command Flow\n\n```\npublish command (provider=agentcube)\n    │\n    ▼\nPublishRuntime.publish()\n    │\n    ├─ _prepare_image_for_publishing()\n    │     └─ DockerService.push_image()\n    │\n    ├─ _publish_cr_to_k8s()\n    │     └─ AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime()\n    │\n    └─ _update_publish_metadata()\n          └─ MetadataService.update_metadata()\n\npublish command (provider=k8s)\n    │\n    ▼\nPublishRuntime.publish()\n    │\n    ├─ _prepare_image_for_publishing()\n    │\n    ├─ _publish_k8s()\n    │     └─ KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent()\n    │\n    └─ _update_publish_metadata()\n          └─ MetadataService.update_metadata()\n```\n\n## 5. Validation Rules\n\n### 5.1 Workspace Validation\n\n| Scenario | Rule | Error |\n|----------|------|-------|\n| Path not exists | Must be valid directory | `ValueError(\"Directory does not exist\")` |\n| Python workspace | Must have `*.py` files | `ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")` |\n| Java workspace | Must have `pom.xml` | `ValueError(\"No pom.xml found in workspace\")` |\n\n### 5.2 Metadata Validation\n\n| Field | Rule | Error |\n|-------|------|-------|\n| `language` | Must be `python` or `java` (case-insensitive) | `ValueError` |\n| `build_mode` | Must be `local` or `cloud` (case-insensitive) | `ValueError` |\n| `port` | Must be 1-65535 | `ValueError` |\n| `agent_name` | Required, non-empty | `ValidationError` |\n| `entrypoint` | Required, non-empty | `ValidationError` |\n\n### 5.3 Provider-Specific Validation\n\n**AgentCube provider requires:**\n- `router_url` in metadata\n- `workload_manager_url` in metadata\n- `readiness_probe_path` in metadata (for AgentRuntime CR)\n- `readiness_probe_port` in metadata (for AgentRuntime CR)\n\n**Error:** `ValueError(\"router_url and workload_manager_url are required in agent_metadata.yaml\")`\n\n## 6. Runtime Class Integration\n\n### 6.1 PackRuntime\n\n```python\nclass PackRuntime:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n        self._metadata_service = MetadataService(verbose=verbose)\n        self._docker_service = DockerService(verbose=verbose)\n\n    def pack(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        # Validate workspace\n        self._validate_workspace_structure(workspace_path)\n        \n        # Load/create metadata\n        metadata = self._load_or_create_metadata(workspace_path, options)\n        \n        # Apply CLI overrides\n        metadata = self._apply_option_overrides(metadata, options)\n        \n        # Validate language compatibility\n        self._validate_language_compatibility(workspace_path, metadata)\n        \n        # Process dependencies\n        self._process_dependencies(workspace_path, metadata)\n        \n        # Generate Dockerfile if needed\n        dockerfile_path = self._generate_dockerfile(workspace_path, metadata)\n        \n        # Save metadata\n        self._update_pack_metadata(workspace_path, metadata, dockerfile_path)\n        \n        return {\n            \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n            \"workspace_path\": str(workspace_path),\n            \"metadata_path\": str(workspace_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"),\n        }\n```\n\n### 6.2 Metadata Update Scenarios\n\n| Command | Updated Fields |\n|---------|----------------|\n| `pack` | All fields (initial save) |\n| `build` | `version` (incremented), `image` (build info) |\n| `publish` | `agent_id`, `agent_endpoint`, `k8s_deployment` |\n\n## 7. Error Handling\n\n### 7.1 Metadata Load Errors\n\n| Error | Handling |\n|-------|----------|\n| File not found | Create default metadata |\n| YAML parse error | Raise `ValueError(\"Invalid metadata file\")` |\n| Validation error | Raise with field-specific message |\n\n### 7.2 Metadata Save Errors\n\n| Error | Handling |\n|-------|----------|\n| Directory not writable | Raise `IOError(\"Cannot write to workspace\")` |\n| YAML dump error | Raise `ValueError(\"Failed to serialize metadata\")` |\n\n## 8. Testing Strategy\n\n### 8.1 Unit Tests\n\n```python\nimport pytest\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom agentcube.services.metadata_service import MetadataService\nfrom agentcube.models.pack_models import MetadataOptions, AgentMetadata\n\ndef test_load_metadata_with_fallback(tmp_path):\n    \"\"\"Test metadata load fallback from agent.yaml.\"\"\"\n    (tmp_path / \"agent.yaml\").write_text(\"\"\"\nagent_name: test-agent\nlanguage: python\nentrypoint: python main.py\n\"\"\")\n    service = MetadataService()\n    metadata = service.load_metadata(tmp_path)\n    assert metadata.agent_name == \"test-agent\"\n\ndef test_save_metadata_exclude_none(tmp_path):\n    \"\"\"Test that None values are excluded from saved YAML.\"\"\"\n    metadata = AgentMetadata(\n        agent_name=\"test\",\n        entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n    )\n    service = MetadataService()\n    service.save_metadata(tmp_path, metadata)\n    \n    content = (tmp_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\").read_text()\n    assert \"version: null\" not in content\n    assert \"description: null\" not in content\n```\n\n### 8.2 Validation Tests\n\n```python\ndef test_validate_language():\n    \"\"\"Test language validator.\"\"\"\n    with pytest.raises(ValueError):\n        AgentMetadata(language=\"invalid\", entrypoint=\"test\")\n    \n    metadata = AgentMetadata(language=\"PYTHON\", entrypoint=\"test\")\n    assert metadata.language == \"python\"\n\ndef test_validate_port_range():\n    \"\"\"Test port validator.\"\"\"\n    with pytest.raises(ValueError):\n        AgentMetadata(entrypoint=\"test\", port=70000)\n    \n    metadata = AgentMetadata(entrypoint=\"test\", port=8080)\n    assert metadata.port == 8080\n```\n\n---\n\n*Note: The implementation uses `agent_metadata.yaml` as the canonical metadata filename (with `agent.yaml` / `metadata.yaml` fallbacks for load). Documentation that refers to `agentcube.yaml` SHALL be treated as naming drift unless a separate file is introduced in code.*","oldString":"---\n\n*Note: The implementation uses `agent_metadata.yaml` as the canonical metadata filename (with `agent.yaml` / `metadata.yaml` fallbacks for load). Documentation that refers to `agentcube.yaml` SHALL be treated as naming drift unless a separate file is introduced in code.*"},"output":"Edit applied successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"diff":"Index: /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md\n===================================================================\n--- /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md\n+++ /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md\n@@ -2447,6 +2447,425 @@\n ```\n \n ---\n \n+# AR-025 — MetadataService 与数据模型\n+\n+- **AR ID**: AR-025\n+- **Module**: cmd/cli\n+- **Language**: Python\n+- **Size**: M\n+- **Status**: ST-1 Completed (design.md)\n+\n+## 1. Architecture\n+\n+### 1.1 Overview\n+\n+MetadataService provides centralized management of agent metadata throughout the CLI lifecycle. It handles loading, validation, saving, and updating of `AgentMetadata` configuration files that track agent state from packaging through deployment.\n+\n+### 1.2 Package Structure\n+\n+```\n+agentcube/\n+├── models/\n+│   └── pack_models.py          # MetadataOptions dataclass\n+├── services/\n+│   └── metadata_service.py      # AgentMetadata, MetadataService\n+└── runtime/\n+    └── pack_runtime.py         # Uses MetadataService\n+```\n+\n+## 2. Data Models\n+\n+### 2.1 AgentMetadata (Pydantic BaseModel)\n+\n+The core data model representing agent configuration and state.\n+\n+```python\n+from pydantic import BaseModel, Field, field_validator\n+from typing import Optional, Dict, Any\n+\n+class AgentMetadata(BaseModel):\n+    agent_name: str = Field(..., description=\"Unique name identifying the agent\")\n+    description: Optional[str] = None\n+    language: str = \"python\"\n+    entrypoint: str = Field(..., description=\"Command to launch the agent\")\n+    port: int = 8080\n+    build_mode: str = \"local\"\n+    region: Optional[str] = None\n+    version: Optional[str] = None\n+    image: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None\n+    auth: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None\n+    requirements_file: Optional[str] = \"requirements.txt\"\n+    registry_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n+    registry_username: Optional[str] = \"\"\n+    registry_password: Optional[str] = \"\"\n+    agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = None\n+    workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None\n+    router_url: Optional[str] = None\n+    readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = None\n+    readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = None\n+    agent_id: Optional[str] = None\n+    session_id: Optional[str] = None\n+    k8s_deployment: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None\n+\n+    @field_validator('language')\n+    @classmethod\n+    def validate_language(cls, v: str) -> str:\n+        valid = ['python', 'java']\n+        if v.lower() not in valid:\n+            raise ValueError(f\"language must be one of {valid}\")\n+        return v.lower()\n+\n+    @field_validator('build_mode')\n+    @classmethod\n+    def validate_build_mode(cls, v: str) -> str:\n+        valid = ['local', 'cloud']\n+        if v.lower() not in valid:\n+            raise ValueError(f\"build_mode must be one of {valid}\")\n+        return v.lower()\n+\n+    @field_validator('port')\n+    @classmethod\n+    def validate_port(cls, v: int) -> int:\n+        if not 1 <= v <= 65535:\n+            raise ValueError(\"port must be between 1 and 65535\")\n+        return v\n+```\n+\n+### 2.2 MetadataOptions (dataclass)\n+\n+CLI options wrapper for passing parameters to runtime classes.\n+\n+```python\n+from dataclasses import dataclass, field\n+from typing import Optional, Dict, Any\n+\n+@dataclass\n+class MetadataOptions:\n+    agent_name: Optional[str] = None\n+    language: Optional[str] = 'python'\n+    entrypoint: Optional[str] = None\n+    port: Optional[int] = 8080\n+    build_mode: Optional[str] = 'local'\n+    requirements_file: Optional[str] = None\n+    description: Optional[str] = None\n+    workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n+    router_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n+    readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = \"\"\n+    readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = 8080\n+    registry_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n+    registry_username: Optional[str] = \"\"\n+    registry_password: Optional[str] = \"\"\n+    agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = \"\"\n+\n+    @classmethod\n+    def from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> \"MetadataOptions\":\n+        \"\"\"Convert CLI options dict to MetadataOptions.\"\"\"\n+        return cls(**{k: v for k, v in options.items() if k in cls.__annotations__})\n+```\n+\n+## 3. MetadataService Implementation\n+\n+### 3.1 Class Definition\n+\n+```python\n+from pathlib import Path\n+from typing import Dict, Any, Optional\n+import yaml\n+import logging\n+\n+class MetadataService:\n+    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n+        self._verbose = verbose\n+        self._logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n+\n+    def load_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> AgentMetadata:\n+        \"\"\"Load metadata from workspace.\n+        \n+        Priority: agent_metadata.yaml > agent.yaml > metadata.yaml\n+        \"\"\"\n+\n+    def save_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n+        \"\"\"Save metadata to agent_metadata.yaml.\"\"\"\n+\n+    def update_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, updates: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata:\n+        \"\"\"Update specific fields in metadata.\"\"\"\n+\n+    def validate_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path) -> bool:\n+        \"\"\"Validate workspace structure.\"\"\"\n+\n+    def _validate_python_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n+        \"\"\"Validate Python-specific workspace requirements.\"\"\"\n+\n+    def _validate_java_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n+        \"\"\"Validate Java-specific workspace requirements.\"\"\"\n+```\n+\n+### 3.2 File Format Specification\n+\n+**Primary filename:** `agent_metadata.yaml`\n+\n+**Fallbacks (load only):**\n+1. `agent_metadata.yaml`\n+2. `agent.yaml`\n+3. `metadata.yaml`\n+\n+**YAML serialization:**\n+\n+```python\n+def save_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n+    metadata_file = workspace_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n+    with open(metadata_file, 'w') as f:\n+        yaml.dump(\n+            metadata.model_dump(exclude_none=True),\n+            f,\n+            default_flow_style=False,\n+            indent=2,\n+            sort_keys=False,\n+        )\n+```\n+\n+### 3.3 Load Fallback Logic\n+\n+```python\n+def load_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> AgentMetadata:\n+    for filename in ['agent_metadata.yaml', 'agent.yaml', 'metadata.yaml']:\n+        metadata_file = workspace_path / filename\n+        if metadata_file.exists():\n+            with open(metadata_file) as f:\n+                data = yaml.safe_load(f)\n+            return AgentMetadata(**data)\n+    \n+    # Return default if no file found\n+    return AgentMetadata(\n+        agent_name=workspace_path.name,\n+        language=\"python\",\n+        entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n+    )\n+```\n+\n+## 4. CLI Integration\n+\n+### 4.1 Pack Command Flow\n+\n+```\n+pack command\n+    │\n+    ▼\n+PackRuntime.pack()\n+    │\n+    ├─ _validate_workspace_structure()\n+    │     └─ MetadataService.validate_workspace()\n+    │\n+    ├─ _load_or_create_metadata()\n+    │     └─ MetadataService.load_metadata()\n+    │\n+    ├─ _apply_option_overrides()\n+    │     └─ CLI options override metadata fields\n+    │\n+    └─ _update_pack_metadata()\n+          └─ MetadataService.save_metadata()\n+```\n+\n+### 4.2 Build Command Flow\n+\n+```\n+build command\n+    │\n+    ▼\n+BuildRuntime.build()\n+    │\n+    ├─ _increment_version()\n+    │     └─ Update metadata.version\n+    │\n+    ├─ _build_local()\n+    │     └─ DockerService.build_image()\n+    │\n+    └─ _update_build_metadata()\n+          └─ MetadataService.update_metadata()\n+```\n+\n+### 4.3 Publish Command Flow\n+\n+```\n+publish command (provider=agentcube)\n+    │\n+    ▼\n+PublishRuntime.publish()\n+    │\n+    ├─ _prepare_image_for_publishing()\n+    │     └─ DockerService.push_image()\n+    │\n+    ├─ _publish_cr_to_k8s()\n+    │     └─ AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime()\n+    │\n+    └─ _update_publish_metadata()\n+          └─ MetadataService.update_metadata()\n+\n+publish command (provider=k8s)\n+    │\n+    ▼\n+PublishRuntime.publish()\n+    │\n+    ├─ _prepare_image_for_publishing()\n+    │\n+    ├─ _publish_k8s()\n+    │     └─ KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent()\n+    │\n+    └─ _update_publish_metadata()\n+          └─ MetadataService.update_metadata()\n+```\n+\n+## 5. Validation Rules\n+\n+### 5.1 Workspace Validation\n+\n+| Scenario | Rule | Error |\n+|----------|------|-------|\n+| Path not exists | Must be valid directory | `ValueError(\"Directory does not exist\")` |\n+| Python workspace | Must have `*.py` files | `ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")` |\n+| Java workspace | Must have `pom.xml` | `ValueError(\"No pom.xml found in workspace\")` |\n+\n+### 5.2 Metadata Validation\n+\n+| Field | Rule | Error |\n+|-------|------|-------|\n+| `language` | Must be `python` or `java` (case-insensitive) | `ValueError` |\n+| `build_mode` | Must be `local` or `cloud` (case-insensitive) | `ValueError` |\n+| `port` | Must be 1-65535 | `ValueError` |\n+| `agent_name` | Required, non-empty | `ValidationError` |\n+| `entrypoint` | Required, non-empty | `ValidationError` |\n+\n+### 5.3 Provider-Specific Validation\n+\n+**AgentCube provider requires:**\n+- `router_url` in metadata\n+- `workload_manager_url` in metadata\n+- `readiness_probe_path` in metadata (for AgentRuntime CR)\n+- `readiness_probe_port` in metadata (for AgentRuntime CR)\n+\n+**Error:** `ValueError(\"router_url and workload_manager_url are required in agent_metadata.yaml\")`\n+\n+## 6. Runtime Class Integration\n+\n+### 6.1 PackRuntime\n+\n+```python\n+class PackRuntime:\n+    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n+        self._metadata_service = MetadataService(verbose=verbose)\n+        self._docker_service = DockerService(verbose=verbose)\n+\n+    def pack(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n+        # Validate workspace\n+        self._validate_workspace_structure(workspace_path)\n+        \n+        # Load/create metadata\n+        metadata = self._load_or_create_metadata(workspace_path, options)\n+        \n+        # Apply CLI overrides\n+        metadata = self._apply_option_overrides(metadata, options)\n+        \n+        # Validate language compatibility\n+        self._validate_language_compatibility(workspace_path, metadata)\n+        \n+        # Process dependencies\n+        self._process_dependencies(workspace_path, metadata)\n+        \n+        # Generate Dockerfile if needed\n+        dockerfile_path = self._generate_dockerfile(workspace_path, metadata)\n+        \n+        # Save metadata\n+        self._update_pack_metadata(workspace_path, metadata, dockerfile_path)\n+        \n+        return {\n+            \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n+            \"workspace_path\": str(workspace_path),\n+            \"metadata_path\": str(workspace_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"),\n+        }\n+```\n+\n+### 6.2 Metadata Update Scenarios\n+\n+| Command | Updated Fields |\n+|---------|----------------|\n+| `pack` | All fields (initial save) |\n+| `build` | `version` (incremented), `image` (build info) |\n+| `publish` | `agent_id`, `agent_endpoint`, `k8s_deployment` |\n+\n+## 7. Error Handling\n+\n+### 7.1 Metadata Load Errors\n+\n+| Error | Handling |\n+|-------|----------|\n+| File not found | Create default metadata |\n+| YAML parse error | Raise `ValueError(\"Invalid metadata file\")` |\n+| Validation error | Raise with field-specific message |\n+\n+### 7.2 Metadata Save Errors\n+\n+| Error | Handling |\n+|-------|----------|\n+| Directory not writable | Raise `IOError(\"Cannot write to workspace\")` |\n+| YAML dump error | Raise `ValueError(\"Failed to serialize metadata\")` |\n+\n+## 8. Testing Strategy\n+\n+### 8.1 Unit Tests\n+\n+```python\n+import pytest\n+from pathlib import Path\n+from agentcube.services.metadata_service import MetadataService\n+from agentcube.models.pack_models import MetadataOptions, AgentMetadata\n+\n+def test_load_metadata_with_fallback(tmp_path):\n+    \"\"\"Test metadata load fallback from agent.yaml.\"\"\"\n+    (tmp_path / \"agent.yaml\").write_text(\"\"\"\n+agent_name: test-agent\n+language: python\n+entrypoint: python main.py\n+\"\"\")\n+    service = MetadataService()\n+    metadata = service.load_metadata(tmp_path)\n+    assert metadata.agent_name == \"test-agent\"\n+\n+def test_save_metadata_exclude_none(tmp_path):\n+    \"\"\"Test that None values are excluded from saved YAML.\"\"\"\n+    metadata = AgentMetadata(\n+        agent_name=\"test\",\n+        entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n+    )\n+    service = MetadataService()\n+    service.save_metadata(tmp_path, metadata)\n+    \n+    content = (tmp_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\").read_text()\n+    assert \"version: null\" not in content\n+    assert \"description: null\" not in content\n+```\n+\n+### 8.2 Validation Tests\n+\n+```python\n+def test_validate_language():\n+    \"\"\"Test language validator.\"\"\"\n+    with pytest.raises(ValueError):\n+        AgentMetadata(language=\"invalid\", entrypoint=\"test\")\n+    \n+    metadata = AgentMetadata(language=\"PYTHON\", entrypoint=\"test\")\n+    assert metadata.language == \"python\"\n+\n+def test_validate_port_range():\n+    \"\"\"Test port validator.\"\"\"\n+    with pytest.raises(ValueError):\n+        AgentMetadata(entrypoint=\"test\", port=70000)\n+    \n+    metadata = AgentMetadata(entrypoint=\"test\", port=8080)\n+    assert metadata.port == 8080\n+```\n+\n+---\n+\n *Note: The implementation uses `agent_metadata.yaml` as the canonical metadata filename (with `agent.yaml` / `metadata.yaml` fallbacks for load). Documentation that refers to `agentcube.yaml` SHALL be treated as naming drift unless a separate file is introduced in code.*\n ```\n\\ No newline at end of file\n","filediff":{"file":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md","before":"# AR-021 — CLI Build Command\n\n- **AR ID**: AR-021\n- **Module**: cmd/cli\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n- **Status**: ST-1 Completed (design.md)\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Overview\n\nAgentCube CLI (`kubectl-agentcube`) is a Python-based command-line tool for packaging, building, publishing, invoking, and checking status of AI agents against AgentCube or standard Kubernetes. The CLI uses Typer for command parsing and provides a rich user experience with Rich library.\n\n### 1.2 Package Structure\n\n```\ncmd/cli/\n├── pyproject.toml                              # Project metadata, dependencies, console script mapping\n├── agentcube/\n│   ├── __init__.py                             # Package version __version__, exports app, runtimes\n│   ├── cli/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py                         # CLI subpackage marker\n│   │   └── main.py                             # Typer app, all commands, _handle_error, version_callback\n│   ├── models/\n│   │   └── pack_models.py                      # MetadataOptions dataclass\n│   ├── runtime/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py                         # Re-exports runtimes + MetadataOptions\n│   │   ├── pack_runtime.py                     # PackRuntime\n│   │   ├── build_runtime.py                    # BuildRuntime\n│   │   ├── publish_runtime.py                  # PublishRuntime\n│   │   ├── invoke_runtime.py                   # InvokeRuntime\n│   │   └── status_runtime.py                   # StatusRuntime\n│   ├── services/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py                         # Services package docstring\n│   │   ├── metadata_service.py                 # AgentMetadata, MetadataService\n│   │   ├── docker_service.py                   # DockerService\n│   │   ├── k8s_provider.py                     # KubernetesProvider\n│   │   └── agentcube_provider.py               # AgentCubeProvider\n│   └── operations/\n│       └── __init__.py                         # Placeholder module docstring\n└── examples/\n    ├── hello-agent/\n    │   └── main.py                             # Example agent\n    └── math-agent/\n        └── main.py                             # Example agent\n```\n\n### 1.3 Console Script Entry Point\n\n```toml\n[project.scripts]\nkubectl-agentcube = \"agentcube.cli.main:app\"\n```\n\nThe CLI is invoked as `kubectl-agentcube` with subcommands: `pack`, `build`, `publish`, `invoke`, `status`.\n\n## 2. Command Specifications\n\n### 2.1 Global Options\n\nThe root callback accepts:\n\n| Option | Type | Default | Description |\n|--------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--version` | Optional[bool] | None | Show version and exit (eager option) |\n| `--verbose`, `-v` | bool | False | Enable verbose output |\n\n**Version Output**: `AgentCube CLI (kubectl agentcube) version: {__version__}` using Rich markup.\n\n**Verbose Behavior**: When `--verbose` is passed, `logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)` is called.\n\n### 2.2 pack Command\n\nValidates and prepares a workspace, merges CLI overrides into metadata, optionally generates a Dockerfile.\n\n```python\ndef pack(\n    workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\"),\n    agent_name: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--agent-name\", help=\"Override the agent name\"),\n    language: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--language\", help=\"Programming language (python, java)\"),\n    entrypoint: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--entrypoint\", help=\"Override the entrypoint command\"),\n    port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--port\", help=\"Port to expose in the Dockerfile\"),\n    build_mode: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--build-mode\", help=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\"),\n    description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"),\n    output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for packaged workspace\"),\n    verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n) -> None:\n```\n\n**Success Output**: Prints success with `agent_name`, resolved `workspace_path`, and `metadata_path` using Rich `Progress` spinner.\n\n### 2.3 build Command\n\nBuilds a container image from a packaged workspace using local Docker when `build_mode` is `local`.\n\n```python\ndef build(\n    workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\"),\n    proxy: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"-p\", \"--proxy\", help=\"Custom proxy URL for dependency resolution\"),\n    cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--cloud-provider\", help=\"Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\"),\n    output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for build artifacts\"),\n    verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n) -> None:\n```\n\n**Version Increment**: Increments `metadata.version` (patch bump for X.Y.Z, or append .1 / fallback {version}-1) before build and reverts on failure.\n\n### 2.4 publish Command\n\nPublishes/deploys using provider `agentcube` (AgentRuntime CR) or `k8s` (Deployment + NodePort Service).\n\n```python\ndef publish(\n    workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\"),\n    version: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--version\", help=\"Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0)\"),\n    image_url: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-url\", help=\"Image repository URL\"),\n    image_username: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-username\", help=\"Username for image repository\"),\n    image_password: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-password\", help=\"Password for image repository\"),\n    description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"),\n    region: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--region\", help=\"Deployment region\"),\n    cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--cloud-provider\", help=\"Cloud provider name\"),\n    provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' or 'k8s'\"),\n    node_port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--node-port\", help=\"NodePort (30000-32767)\"),\n    replicas: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--replicas\", help=\"Number of replicas\"),\n    namespace: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--namespace\", help=\"Deployment namespace\"),\n    verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n) -> None:\n```\n\n### 2.5 invoke Command\n\nPOSTs JSON to the published agent endpoint.\n\n```python\ndef invoke(\n    workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\"),\n    payload: str = typer.Option(\"{}\", \"--payload\", help=\"JSON-formatted input passed to the agent\"),\n    header_list: Optional[List[str]] = typer.Option(None, \"--header\", help=\"Custom HTTP headers\"),\n    provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' or 'k8s'\"),\n    verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n) -> None:\n```\n\n**Header Format**: Headers are parsed as `key:value` format. Invalid format prints error and exits with code 1.\n\n**Session Header**: If metadata contains `session_id`, adds header `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` to request.\n\n### 2.6 status Command\n\nLoads workspace metadata and displays agent status in a Rich `Table`.\n\n```python\ndef status(\n    workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\"),\n    provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' or 'k8s'\"),\n    verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n) -> None:\n```\n\n**Exit Codes**: Exits with code 1 when status is `not_published` or `error`.\n\n## 3. Runtime Classes\n\n### 3.1 PackRuntime\n\nHandles workspace validation, metadata loading/creation, Dockerfile generation.\n\n```python\nclass PackRuntime:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n    def pack(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def _validate_workspace_structure(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n    def _load_or_create_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n    def _apply_option_overrides(self, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n    def _validate_language_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n    def _validate_python_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n    def _validate_java_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n    def _process_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n    def _generate_dockerfile(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Optional[Path]: ...\n```\n\n### 3.2 BuildRuntime\n\nManages Docker image build process with local and cloud modes.\n\n```python\nclass BuildRuntime:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n    def build(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def _increment_version(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata) -> Any: ...\n    def _validate_build_prerequisites(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n    def _build_local(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def _build_cloud(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n```\n\n### 3.3 PublishRuntime\n\nHandles deployment to AgentCube or Kubernetes.\n\n```python\nclass PublishRuntime:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n    def publish(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def _publish_cr_to_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def _publish_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def _prepare_image_for_publishing(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n```\n\n### 3.4 InvokeRuntime\n\nHandles agent invocation via HTTP.\n\n```python\nclass InvokeRuntime:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n    def invoke(self, workspace_path: Path, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None) -> Any: ...\n    async def _invoke_agent_via_agentcube(self, agent_id: str, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]], endpoint: str, workspace_path: Path) -> Any: ...\n    async def _direct_http_invocation(self, endpoint: str, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]], workspace_path: Path) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n```\n\n**Known Issue**: `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube` may raise `UnboundLocalError` if `endpoint` doesn't start with `http`.\n\n### 3.5 StatusRuntime\n\nRetrieves and displays agent status.\n\n```python\nclass StatusRuntime:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n    def get_status(self, workspace_path: Path, provider: Optional[str] = None) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def _get_k8s_status(self, metadata) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def _get_cr_k8s_status(self, metadata) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n```\n\n## 4. Services\n\n### 4.1 DockerService\n\n```python\nclass DockerService:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n    def check_docker_available(self) -> bool: ...\n    def build_image(self, dockerfile_path: Path, context_path: Path, image_name: str, tag: str = \"latest\", build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n    def get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n    def push_image(self, image_name: str, registry_url: Optional[str] = None, username: Optional[str] = None, password: Optional[str] = None) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n    def remove_image(self, image_name: str) -> bool: ...\n```\n\n### 4.2 MetadataService\n\n```python\nclass MetadataService:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n    def load_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n    def save_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n    def update_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, updates: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n    def validate_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path) -> bool: ...\n```\n\n**Metadata File**: Saved to `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml` using `yaml.dump` with `default_flow_style=False`, `indent=2`.\n\n### 4.3 KubernetesProvider\n\n```python\nclass KubernetesProvider:\n    def __init__(self, namespace: str = \"default\", verbose: bool = False, kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None) -> None: ...\n    def deploy_agent(self, agent_name: str, image_url: str, port: int, entrypoint: Optional[str] = None, replicas: int = 1, node_port: Optional[int] = None, env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def wait_for_deployment_ready(self, name: str, timeout: int = 120) -> None: ...\n    def get_agent_status(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def delete_agent(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n```\n\n### 4.4 AgentCubeProvider\n\n```python\nclass AgentCubeProvider:\n    def __init__(self, namespace: str = \"default\", verbose: bool = False, kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None) -> None: ...\n    def deploy_agent_runtime(self, agent_name: str, image_url: str, port: int, entrypoint: Optional[str] = None, env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None, workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None, router_url: Optional[str] = None, readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = None, readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = None) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def get_agent_runtime(self, name: str, namespace: str) -> Optional[Dict[str, Any]]: ...\n```\n\n**CR API**: `group=\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"`, `version=\"v1alpha1\"`, `plural=\"agentruntimes\"`.\n\n## 5. Data Models\n\n### 5.1 AgentMetadata (Pydantic BaseModel)\n\n| Field | Type | Default | Description |\n|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `agent_name` | str | (required) | Unique name identifying the agent |\n| `description` | Optional[str] | None | Human-readable summary |\n| `language` | str | \"python\" | Programming language used |\n| `entrypoint` | str | (required) | Command to launch the agent |\n| `port` | int | 8080 | Port exposed by the agent runtime |\n| `build_mode` | str | \"local\" | Build strategy: local or cloud |\n| `region` | Optional[str] | None | Deployment region |\n| `version` | Optional[str] | None | Semantic version string for publishing |\n| `image` | Optional[Dict[str, Any]] | None | Container image information |\n| `auth` | Optional[Dict[str, Any]] | None | Authentication configuration |\n| `requirements_file` | Optional[str] | \"requirements.txt\" | Python dependency file |\n| `registry_url` | Optional[str] | \"\" | Registry URL for image publishing |\n| `registry_username` | Optional[str] | \"\" | Registry username |\n| `registry_password` | Optional[str] | \"\" | Registry password |\n| `agent_endpoint` | Optional[str] | None | Agent endpoint URL |\n| `workload_manager_url` | Optional[str] | None | URL for the Workload Manager |\n| `router_url` | Optional[str] | None | URL for the Router |\n| `readiness_probe_path` | Optional[str] | None | Path for the readiness probe |\n| `readiness_probe_port` | Optional[int] | None | Port for the readiness probe |\n| `agent_id` | Optional[str] | None | Agent ID assigned by AgentCube |\n| `session_id` | Optional[str] | None | The session ID for the agent |\n| `k8s_deployment` | Optional[Dict[str, Any]] | None | Kubernetes deployment information |\n\n**Validators**:\n- `validate_language`: ['python', 'java'] lowercase\n- `validate_build_mode`: ['local', 'cloud'] lowercase\n- `validate_port`: 1..65535\n\n### 5.2 MetadataOptions (dataclass)\n\n| Field | Type | Default |\n|-------|------|---------|\n| `agent_name` | Optional[str] | None |\n| `language` | Optional[str] | 'python' |\n| `entrypoint` | Optional[str] | None |\n| `port` | Optional[int] | 8080 |\n| `build_mode` | Optional[str] | 'local' |\n| `requirements_file` | Optional[str] | None |\n| `description` | Optional[str] | None |\n| `workload_manager_url` | Optional[str] | \"\" |\n| `router_url` | Optional[str] | \"\" |\n| `readiness_probe_path` | Optional[str] | \"\" |\n| `readiness_probe_port` | Optional[int] | 8080 |\n| `registry_url` | Optional[str] | \"\" |\n| `registry_username` | Optional[str] | \"\" |\n| `registry_password` | Optional[str] | \"\" |\n| `agent_endpoint` | Optional[str] | \"\" |\n\n## 6. Dependencies\n\n### 6.1 Required Dependencies\n\n```toml\ndependencies = [\n    \"typer[all]>=0.9.0\",\n    \"pydantic>=2.0.0\",\n    \"pyyaml>=6.0\",\n    \"httpx>=0.24.0\",\n    \"docker>=6.0.0\",\n    \"rich>=13.0.0\",\n    \"packaging>=23.0\",\n    \"importlib-resources>=6.0.0\",\n    \"semver>=3.0.0\",\n]\n```\n\n### 6.2 Optional Dependencies\n\n```toml\n[project.optional-dependencies]\nk8s = [\"kubernetes>=28.0.0\"]\ndev = [\"pytest>=7.4.0\", \"pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0\", \"pytest-cov>=4.1.0\", \"ruff>=0.1.0\", \"mypy>=1.5.0\", \"pre-commit>=3.3.0\", \"kubernetes>=28.0.0\"]\ntest = [\"pytest>=7.4.0\", \"pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0\", \"pytest-cov>=4.1.0\", \"pytest-mock>=3.11.0\", \"httpx-mock>=0.10.0\"]\n```\n\n**Python Version**: `requires-python = \">=3.10\"`\n\n## 7. Error Handling\n\n### 7.1 Error Handler Function\n\n```python\ndef _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None:\n    # prints \"Error {command_name}: {e}\" in red\n    # if verbose, prints full traceback\n    # raises typer.Exit(1)\n```\n\n### 7.2 Common Errors\n\n| Error | Scenario | Exit Code |\n|-------|----------|-----------|\n| Workspace not found | Invalid workspace path | 1 |\n| Docker unavailable | build command with local mode | 1 |\n| Invalid payload | invoke with malformed JSON | 1 |\n| Invalid header format | invoke with malformed header | 1 |\n| Not published | status command with no agent_id | 1 |\n\n## 8. Testing Strategy\n\n### 8.1 Unit Tests\n\nTest each runtime class and service with mocked dependencies.\n\n### 8.2 Integration Tests\n\n- End-to-end CLI command tests\n- Docker integration tests (requires Docker)\n- K8s integration tests (requires test cluster)\n\n### 8.3 Build Verification\n\n```bash\n# Install CLI\npip install -e cmd/cli/\n\n# Verify entry point\nkubectl-agentcube --help\n\n# Run tests\npytest cmd/cli/tests/ -v\n```\n\n---\n\n# AR-019 — CLI Binary Entry Points (4 Binaries)\n\n- **AR ID**: AR-019\n- **Module**: cmd\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: M\n- **Status**: ST-1 Completed (design.md)\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Overview\n\nAgentCube provides four CLI binary entry points for its Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform. Each binary serves a distinct role in the system architecture, communicating via the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group using the generated client-go library.\n\n### 1.2 Binary Overview\n\n| Binary | Purpose | Port | Dependencies |\n|--------|---------|------|--------------|\n| `agentd` | K8s Reconciler Controller | N/A | K8s API Server, etcd |\n| `picod` | Code Execution Daemon | 8080 (configurable) | Local filesystem |\n| `router` | HTTP Session Router | 8080 | Redis/Valkey, WorkloadManager |\n| `workload-manager` | Sandbox Lifecycle Manager | 8080 | K8s API Server, Redis/Valkey |\n\n### 1.3 Component Structure\n\n```\ncmd/\n├── agentd/\n│   ├── main.go                      # Controller entry point\n│   └── ...\n├── picod/\n│   ├── main.go                      # Code execution daemon entry\n│   └── ...\n├── router/\n│   ├── main.go                      # Router entry point\n│   └── ...\n└── workload-manager/\n    ├── main.go                      # Workload manager entry point\n    └── ...\n```\n\n### 1.4 Architecture Diagram\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                              AgentCube System                                │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                                                                             │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │                        agentd (Controller)                           │   │\n│  │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │   │\n│  │  │  Watches: AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter CRDs                 │  │   │\n│  │  │  Creates: Pods, Services, ConfigMaps                          │  │   │\n│  │  │  Status Updates: AgentRuntimeStatus, CodeInterpreterStatus    │  │   │\n│  │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │   │\n│  └──────────────────────────────┬────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n│                                 │                                             │\n│                                 │ K8s API                                     │\n│                                 ▼                                             │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │                    Kubernetes API Server                             │   │\n│  │  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌────────────────────┐   │   │\n│  │  │ AgentRuntime    │  │ CodeInterpreter │  │ Pod/Service/Config │   │   │\n│  │  │ (CRD)          │  │ (CRD)           │  │ (Native resources)│   │   │\n│  │  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘  └────────────────────┘   │   │\n│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n│                                    │                                         │\n├────────────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                                    │                                         │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────┴─────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │                    workload-manager                                 │   │\n│  │  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────┐   │   │\n│  │  │ HTTP API    │  │ Sandbox CRUD │  │ Session Lifecycle       │   │   │\n│  │  │ (Gin)       │  │              │  │                         │   │   │\n│  │  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────────────────┘   │   │\n│  └──────────────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n│                                 │                                           │\n│                                 │ Session events                            │\n│                                 ▼                                           │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │                    Redis/Valkey (Session Store)                     │   │\n│  │  - Session data (session-routing)                                   │   │\n│  │  - Sandbox state                                                    │   │\n│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n│                                    │                                         │\n│                                    │ Proxy routing                           │\n│                                    ▼                                         │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │                         router                                      │   │\n│  │  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────┐   │   │\n│  │  │ Session     │  │ Auth/JWT    │  │ Backend Health Check    │   │   │\n│  │  │ Routing     │  │ Middleware  │  │                          │   │   │\n│  │  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────────────────┘   │   │\n│  └──────────────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n│                                 │                                           │\n│                                 │ HTTP Requests                             │\n│                                 ▼                                           │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │                      Sandbox Pods                                   │   │\n│  │  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────┐   │   │\n│  │  │ Agent        │  │ Code         │  │ Services                 │   │   │\n│  │  │ Container    │  │ Interpreter  │  │ (NodePort/ClusterIP)    │   │   │\n│  │  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────────────────┘   │   │\n│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n│                                    │                                         │\n│                                    │ Optional                                │\n│                                    ▼                                         │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │                         picod                                       │   │\n│  │  - Code execution daemon inside sandbox pods                       │   │\n│  │  - File operations, execution                                       │   │\n│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n│                                                                             │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### 1.5 Data Flow\n\n```\n                                    ┌─────────────────┐\n                                    │   Client Request│\n                                    └────────┬────────┘\n                                             │\n                                             ▼\n                               ┌─────────────────────────┐\n                               │      router             │\n                               │  ┌───────────────────┐  │\n                               │  │ Auth Middleware   │  │\n                               │  │ JWT/Token Review  │  │\n                               │  └───────────────────┘  │\n                               │            │            │\n                               │            ▼            │\n                               │  ┌───────────────────┐  │\n                               │  │ Session Manager   │  │\n                               │  │ → Redis lookup    │  │\n                               │  └───────────────────┘  │\n                               │            │            │\n                               │            ▼            │\n                               │  ┌───────────────────┐  │\n                               │  │ Backend Selector  │  │\n                               │  │ → WorkloadManager │  │\n                               │  └───────────────────┘  │\n                               └───────────┬─────────────┘\n                                           │\n                                           ▼\n                               ┌─────────────────────────┐\n                               │  workload-manager      │\n                               │  ┌───────────────────┐  │\n                               │  │ API Handlers      │  │\n                               │  │ GET/POST/DELETE   │  │\n                               │  └───────────────────┘  │\n                               │            │            │\n                               │            ▼            │\n                               │  ┌───────────────────┐  │\n                               │  │ Client-go         │  │\n                               │  │ → K8s API         │  │\n                               │  └───────────────────┘  │\n                               └───────────┬─────────────┘\n                                           │\n                                           ▼\n                               ┌─────────────────────────┐\n                               │  Kubernetes API Server  │\n                               │  - Create AgentRuntime │\n                               │  - Create Pod/Service  │\n                               └───────────┬─────────────┘\n                                           │\n                                           ▼\n                               ┌─────────────────────────┐\n                               │      agentd             │\n                               │  ┌───────────────────┐  │\n                               │  │ Controller        │  │\n                               │  │ → Reconcile loop  │  │\n                               │  └───────────────────┘  │\n                               └─────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n## 2. Binary Specifications\n\n### 2.1 agentd — Kubernetes Controller\n\n**Entry Point**: `cmd/agentd/main.go`\n\nThe agentd binary runs as a Kubernetes controller using controller-runtime. It watches `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` custom resources and ensures the desired runtime state matches the actual cluster state.\n\n#### Command-Line Flags\n\n| Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n|------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--metrics-bind-address` | string | \"0\" | Metrics server bind address (0 = disabled) |\n| `--health-probe-bind-address` | string | \"0\" | Health probe bind address |\n| `--leader-elect` | bool | false | Enable leader election |\n| `--leader-elect-lease-duration` | duration | 15s | Leader election lease duration |\n| `--leader-elect-renew-deadline` | duration | 10s | Leader election renew deadline |\n| `--leader-elect-retry-period` | duration | 5s | Leader election retry period |\n\n#### Configuration\n\n```go\ntype AgentdConfig struct {\n    // Metrics server configuration\n    MetricsBindAddress string\n    \n    // Health probe configuration  \n    HealthProbeBindAddress string\n    \n    // Leader election\n    LeaderElect        bool\n    LeaseDuration      time.Duration\n    RenewDeadline      time.Duration\n    RetryPeriod        time.Duration\n    \n    // Namespace to watch (empty = all namespaces)\n    WatchNamespace     string\n    \n    // Sync period for full reconciliation\n    SyncPeriod         time.Duration\n    \n    // Max concurrent reconciles\n    MaxConcurrentReconciles int\n}\n```\n\n#### Dependencies\n\n- `pkg/agentd/` — Controller implementation\n- `pkg/client/informers/` — Generated informers\n- `pkg/client/listers/` — Generated listers\n- `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/` — API types\n\n### 2.2 picod — Code Execution Daemon\n\n**Entry Point**: `cmd/picod/main.go`\n\nThe picod binary runs inside sandbox pods as a code execution daemon, providing file operations and code execution capabilities.\n\n#### Command-Line Flags\n\n| Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n|------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--port` | int | 8080 | Server listen port |\n| `--workspace` | string | \"\" | Root directory for file operations (default: cwd) |\n| `--auth-mode` | string | \"picod\" | Authentication mode: picod, none |\n| `--session-timeout` | duration | 15m | Session timeout |\n| `--max-session-duration` | duration | 8h | Maximum session duration |\n\n#### Configuration\n\n```go\ntype PicoDConfig struct {\n    Port              int\n    Workspace         string\n    AuthMode          string\n    SessionTimeout    time.Duration\n    MaxSessionDuration time.Duration\n}\n```\n\n#### API Endpoints\n\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| GET | `/health` | Health check |\n| POST | `/execute` | Execute code |\n| GET | `/files/*path` | Read file |\n| PUT | `/files/*path` | Write file |\n| DELETE | `/files/*path` | Delete file |\n\n#### Dependencies\n\n- `pkg/picod/` — Server implementation\n\n### 2.3 router — HTTP Session Router\n\n**Entry Point**: `cmd/router/main.go`\n\nThe router binary provides HTTP routing with session management, authentication, and proxy capabilities. It routes incoming requests to the appropriate sandbox backend based on session affinity.\n\n#### Command-Line Flags\n\n| Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n|------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--listen-address` | string | \":8080\" | Server listen address |\n| `--workload-manager-url` | string | \"\" | WorkloadManager backend URL (required) |\n| `--backend-timeout` | duration | 30s | Backend request timeout |\n| `--idle-timeout` | duration | 60s | Idle connection timeout |\n| `--health-check-interval` | duration | 10s | Health check interval |\n| `--health-check-timeout` | duration | 5s | Health check timeout |\n| `--max-conns-per-backend` | int | 100 | Max connections per backend |\n| `--rate-limit-enabled` | bool | false | Enable rate limiting |\n| `--rate-limit-rps` | int | 10 | Rate limit RPS |\n| `--auth-enabled` | bool | false | Enable authentication |\n| `--auth-token` | string | \"\" | Bearer token for auth |\n| `--session-enabled` | bool | false | Enable session management |\n| `--session-timeout` | duration | 30m | Session timeout |\n| `--session-cookie-name` | string | \"AGENTSESSIONID\" | Session cookie name |\n| `--jwt-enabled` | bool | false | Enable JWT authentication |\n| `--jwt-secret` | string | \"\" | JWT secret for HS256 |\n| `--jwt-private-key-path` | string | \"\" | Path to RS256 private key |\n| `--jwt-public-key-path` | string | \"\" | Path to RS256 public key |\n\n#### Configuration\n\n```go\ntype RouterConfig struct {\n    ListenAddress       string\n    WorkloadManagerURL string\n    \n    // Backend\n    BackendTimeout      time.Duration\n    IdleTimeout         time.Duration\n    HealthCheckInterval time.Duration\n    HealthCheckTimeout  time.Duration\n    MaxConnsPerBackend  int\n    \n    // Rate limiting\n    RateLimitEnabled    bool\n    RateLimitRPS        int\n    \n    // Auth\n    AuthEnabled         bool\n    AuthToken           string\n    \n    // Session management\n    SessionEnabled         bool\n    SessionTimeout         time.Duration\n    SessionCookieName      string\n    SessionMaxActive       int\n    SessionCookieSecure    bool\n    SessionCookieHTTPOnly  bool\n    SessionCookieDomain    string\n    SessionCleanupInterval time.Duration\n    \n    // JWT\n    JWTEnabled           bool\n    JWTAlgorithm         string\n    JWTSecret            string\n    JWTPrivateKeyPath    string\n    JWTPublicKeyPath     string\n    JWTIssuer            string\n    JWTAudience          []string\n    JWTExpiration        time.Duration\n    JWTRefreshExpiration time.Duration\n    JWTClockSkew         time.Duration\n    JWTAllowQueryParam   bool\n}\n```\n\n#### Dependencies\n\n- `pkg/router/` — Router implementation\n- `pkg/store/` — Session store (Redis/Valkey)\n- `pkg/client/clientset/` — Generated client-go\n\n### 2.4 workload-manager — Sandbox Lifecycle Manager\n\n**Entry Point**: `cmd/workload-manager/main.go`\n\nThe workload-manager binary provides REST APIs for sandbox lifecycle management. It creates and manages AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources in Kubernetes.\n\n#### Command-Line Flags\n\n| Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n|------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--listen-address` | string | \":8080\" | Server listen address |\n| `--store-type` | string | \"redis\" | Store type: redis, valkey |\n| `--store-address` | string | \"localhost:6379\" | Store address |\n| `--store-password` | string | \"\" | Store password |\n| `--store-db` | int | 0 | Store database number |\n| `--namespace` | string | \"default\" | Default Kubernetes namespace |\n| `--session-timeout` | duration | 15m | Default session timeout |\n| `--max-session-duration` | duration | 8h | Default max session duration |\n| `--gc-interval` | duration | 5m | Garbage collection interval |\n| `--gc-worker-count` | int | 5 | GC worker count |\n\n#### Configuration\n\n```go\ntype WorkloadManagerConfig struct {\n    // Server\n    ListenAddress string\n    \n    // Store (Redis/Valkey)\n    StoreType    string\n    StoreAddress string\n    StorePassword string\n    StoreDB      int\n    \n    // Kubernetes\n    Namespace string\n    \n    // Session defaults\n    SessionTimeout       time.Duration\n    MaxSessionDuration   time.Duration\n    \n    // Garbage collection\n    GCInterval     time.Duration\n    GCWorkerCount  int\n    \n    // Webhook configuration (optional)\n    Webhooks []WebhookConfig\n}\n\ntype WebhookConfig struct {\n    URL        string\n    Timeout    int\n    RetryCount int\n}\n```\n\n#### API Endpoints\n\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| GET | `/health` | Health check |\n| POST | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes` | Create sandbox |\n| GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes` | List sandboxes |\n| GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes/{name}` | Get sandbox |\n| DELETE | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes/{name}` | Delete sandbox |\n| GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes` | List AgentRuntimes |\n| POST | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes` | Create AgentRuntime |\n| GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}` | Get AgentRuntime |\n| DELETE | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}` | Delete AgentRuntime |\n| GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters` | List CodeInterpreters |\n| POST | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters` | Create CodeInterpreter |\n| GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}` | Get CodeInterpreter |\n| DELETE | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}` | Delete CodeInterpreter |\n\n#### Dependencies\n\n- `pkg/workloadmanager/` — Manager implementation\n- `pkg/store/` — Session store (Redis/Valkey)\n- `pkg/client/clientset/` — Generated client-go\n\n## 3. API Contracts\n\n### 3.1 AgentRuntime (CRD)\n\n**API Group**: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`  \n**Version**: `v1alpha1`  \n**Plural**: `agentruntimes`  \n**Short Name**: `ar`\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\nkind: AgentRuntime\nmetadata:\n  name: my-agent\n  namespace: default\nspec:\n  maxSessionDuration: \"8h\"\n  sessionTimeout: \"15m\"\n  targetPorts:\n    - port: 8080\n      protocol: HTTP\n      name: http\n  podTemplate:\n    spec:\n      containers:\n        - name: agent\n          image: my-agent:latest\n          resources:\n            limits:\n              cpu: \"1\"\n              memory: \"1Gi\"\nstatus:\n  phase: Running\n  endpoint: \"http://my-agent.default.sandbox.example.com\"\n  conditions:\n    - type: Ready\n      status: \"True\"\n      lastTransitionTime: \"2024-01-01T00:00:00Z\"\n```\n\n### 3.2 CodeInterpreter (CRD)\n\n**API Group**: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`  \n**Version**: `v1alpha1`  \n**Plural**: `codeinterpreters`  \n**Short Name**: `ci`\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\nkind: CodeInterpreter\nmetadata:\n  name: my-interpreter\n  namespace: default\nspec:\n  authMode: picod\n  maxSessionDuration: \"8h\"\n  sessionTimeout: \"15m\"\n  template:\n    image: python:3.11\n    command: [\"python\", \"-m\", \"picod\"]\n  warmPoolSize: 0\nstatus:\n  phase: Running\n  endpoint: \"http://my-interpreter.default.sandbox.example.com\"\n  ready: true\n```\n\n### 3.3 Client-Go Library Usage\n\n```go\nimport (\n    \"k8s.io/client-go/tools/clientcmd\"\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/client/clientset/versioned\"\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/client/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n)\n\nconfig, _ := clientcmd.BuildConfigFromFlags(\"\", \"\")\nclientset, _ := versioned.NewForConfig(config)\n\n// Create AgentRuntime\narClient := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"default\")\nagentRuntime := &v1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n    // ... spec\n}\nresult, err := arClient.Create(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n\n// List CodeInterpreters\nciClient := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(\"default\")\nlist, err := ciClient.List(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})\n```\n\n## 4. Error Handling\n\n### 4.1 Error Codes\n\n| Code | Name | Description |\n|------|------|-------------|\n| 400 | BadRequest | Invalid request format or parameters |\n| 401 | Unauthorized | Authentication failed |\n| 403 | Forbidden | Insufficient permissions |\n| 404 | NotFound | Resource not found |\n| 409 | Conflict | Resource already exists |\n| 422 | UnprocessableEntity | Validation failed |\n| 429 | TooManyRequests | Rate limit exceeded |\n| 500 | InternalServerError | Internal server error |\n| 502 | BadGateway | Upstream unavailable |\n| 503 | ServiceUnavailable | Service temporarily unavailable |\n| 504 | GatewayTimeout | Upstream timeout |\n\n### 4.2 Error Response Format\n\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": {\n    \"code\": 404,\n    \"message\": \"Resource not found\",\n    \"details\": {\n      \"resource\": \"AgentRuntime\",\n      \"name\": \"my-agent\",\n      \"namespace\": \"default\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### 4.3 Common Errors\n\n| Error | HTTP Code | Retry | Resolution |\n|-------|-----------|-------|------------|\n| SandboxNotFound | 404 | No | Check name/namespace |\n| DeletionFailed | 500 | Yes | Check K8s cluster state |\n| StaleFinalizer | 500 | No | Manual cleanup required |\n| OrphanedResource | 500 | Yes | Force delete |\n| ResourceNotFound | 404 | No | Resource already deleted |\n\n## 5. Testing Strategy\n\n### 5.1 Unit Tests\n\nEach binary should have unit tests for:\n- Configuration parsing\n- Flag handling\n- Error cases\n\n```go\n// Example: router configuration test\nfunc TestRouterConfig(t *testing.T) {\n    tests := []struct {\n        name    string\n        flags   []string\n        wantErr bool\n    }{\n        {\n            name:    \"valid config with required flags\",\n            flags:   []string{\"--workload-manager-url\", \"http://localhost:8080\"},\n            wantErr: false,\n        },\n        {\n            name:    \"missing required flag\",\n            flags:   []string{},\n            wantErr: true,\n        },\n    }\n    \n    for _, tt := range tests {\n        t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n            // Test configuration parsing\n        })\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### 5.2 Integration Tests\n\n- End-to-end binary startup tests\n- K8s client integration tests (requires test cluster)\n- Store integration tests (requires Redis/Valkey)\n\n### 5.3 Build Verification\n\n```bash\n# Build all binaries\ngo build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd\ngo build -o bin/picod ./cmd/picod\ngo build -o bin/router ./cmd/router\ngo build -o bin/workload-manager ./cmd/workload-manager\n\n# Verify binaries exist and are executable\nls -la bin/\n```\n\n## 6. Dependencies\n\n### 6.1 Go Module Dependencies\n\n```\ngithub.com/volcano-sh/agentcube          # Main module\n  ├── k8s.io/api                          # K8s API types\n  ├── k8s.io/apimachinery                 # K8s utilities\n  ├── k8s.io/client-go                   # K8s client\n  ├── k8s.io/klog/v2                     # Logging\n  ├── k8s.io/controller-runtime          # Controller framework\n  ├── github.com/gin-gonic/gin            # HTTP framework\n  ├── github.com/redis/go-redis/v9        # Redis client\n  ├── github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go      # Valkey client\n  ├── github.com/prometheus/client_golang # Metrics\n  └── github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5       # JWT support\n```\n\n### 6.2 External Dependencies\n\n| Component | Requirement | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|-------------|\n| Kubernetes | ≥1.24 | K8s API server |\n| Redis/Valkey | ≥6.0 | Session store |\n| Docker | Optional | For building agent images |\n\n## 7. Configuration Precedence\n\nConfiguration is loaded in the following order (later overrides earlier):\n\n1. Default values (hardcoded)\n2. Environment variables (`AGENTCUBE_*`)\n3. Config file (`/etc/agentcube/config.yaml`)\n4. Command-line flags\n\n### 7.1 Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Binary | Description |\n|----------|--------|-------------|\n| `AGENTCUBE_KUBECONFIG` | all | Path to kubeconfig |\n| `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | all | Default namespace |\n| `AGENTD_METRICS_ADDR` | agentd | Metrics address |\n| `ROUTER_WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | router | Backend URL |\n| `ROUTER_STORE_ADDRESS` | router | Redis/Valkey address |\n| `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_STORE_ADDRESS` | workload-manager | Store address |\n| `PICOD_WORKSPACE` | picod | Workspace directory |\n\n### 7.2 Config File Format\n\n```yaml\n# /etc/agentcube/config.yaml\napiVersion: v1\nkind: AgentCubeConfig\nmetadata:\n  name: agentcube\nspec:\n  namespace: default\n  session:\n    timeout: 15m\n    maxDuration: 8h\n  store:\n    type: redis\n    address: localhost:6379\n    password: \"\"\n  router:\n    listenAddress: \":8080\"\n    workloadManagerURL: \"http://localhost:8081\"\n  workloadManager:\n    listenAddress: \":8081\"\n```\n\n## 8. Deployment\n\n### 8.1 Docker Images\n\nEach binary is packaged as a separate Docker image:\n\n```dockerfile\n# For agentd, router, workload-manager\nFROM golang:1.24-alpine AS builder\nWORKDIR /build\nCOPY go.mod go.sum ./\nRUN go mod download\nCOPY . .\nRUN CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux go build -o /agentd ./cmd/agentd\n\nFROM alpine:3.19\nRUN apk --no-cache add ca-certificates\nCOPY --from=builder /agentd /agentd\nENTRYPOINT [\"/agentd\"]\n```\n\n### 8.2 Kubernetes Deployment\n\nThe system can be deployed using Helm:\n\n```yaml\n# values.yaml\nagentd:\n  enabled: true\n  replicas: 1\n  \nrouter:\n  enabled: true\n  replicas: 2\n  service:\n    type: NodePort\n    port: 80\n    \nworkloadManager:\n  enabled: true\n  replicas: 2\n  \npicod:\n  enabled: true  # Deployed as sidecar in sandbox pods\n\n---\n\n# AR-022 — CLI Publish Command\n\n- **AR ID**: AR-022\n- **Module**: cmd/cli\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: L\n\n---\n\n## 9. CLI Toolkit Specification\n\n### Purpose\n\nCommand-line tool (`kubectl-agentcube`) for packaging, building, publishing, invoking, and checking status of AI agents against AgentCube or standard Kubernetes.\n\n### Requirements\n\n#### Requirement: Global CLI options\nThe system SHALL expose a Typer application named `agentcube` with global options on the root callback.\n\n##### Scenario: Version display\n- **GIVEN** the CLI is installed and importable\n- **WHEN** the user passes `--version` (eager option, `Optional[bool]`, default `None`)\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print `AgentCube CLI (kubectl agentcube) version: {__version__}` (Rich markup) and exit without running a subcommand (`typer.Exit()`), where `__version__` is `0.1.0` from `agentcube.__init__`\n\n##### Scenario: Global verbose logging\n- **GIVEN** the user passes `--verbose` / `-v` (`bool`, default `False`) on the root callback\n- **WHEN** the callback runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)`\n\n#### Requirement: `pack` command\nThe system SHALL provide `pack` to validate and prepare a workspace, merge CLI overrides into metadata, optionally generate a `Dockerfile`, and report paths.\n\n##### Scenario: Options and defaults\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `pack`\n- **WHEN** options are omitted\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL use: `workspace` = `\".\"` (`-f` / `--workspace`, `str`); `agent_name` = `None` (`--agent-name`, `Optional[str]`); `language` = `None` (`--language`); `entrypoint` = `None` (`--entrypoint`); `port` = `None` (`--port`, `Optional[int]`); `build_mode` = `None` (`--build-mode`); `description` = `None` (`--description`); `output` = `None` (`--output`); `verbose` = `False` (`--verbose`, command-local)\n\n##### Scenario: Successful pack\n- **GIVEN** a valid workspace path\n- **WHEN** `pack` completes without exception\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print success with `agent_name`, resolved `workspace_path`, and `metadata_path` (reported as `{final_workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml`), using a Rich `Progress` spinner during work\n\n##### Scenario: Pack failure handling\n- **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack` raises\n- **WHEN** `verbose` is `True`\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print `Error packaging agent: {e}` in red, print a full traceback, and exit with code `1`\n\n#### Requirement: `build` command\nThe system SHALL build a container image from a packaged workspace using local Docker when `build_mode` is `local` (default in metadata), with optional proxy and tag derived from metadata version.\n\n##### Scenario: Options and defaults\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `build`\n- **WHEN** options are omitted\n- **THEN** defaults SHALL be: `workspace` = `\".\"` (`-f` / `--workspace`); `proxy` = `None` (`-p` / `--proxy`); `cloud_provider` = `None` (`--cloud-provider`); `output` = `None` (`--output`); `verbose` = `False` (`--verbose`)\n\n##### Scenario: Local Docker build prerequisites\n- **GIVEN** `build_mode` resolves to `local`\n- **WHEN** Docker is unavailable\n- **THEN** `BuildRuntime` SHALL raise `RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")` surfaced via CLI error handling\n\n##### Scenario: Version increment on build\n- **GIVEN** a successful local build path\n- **WHEN** `BuildRuntime.build` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL increment `metadata.version` (patch bump for `X.Y.Z`, or append `.1` / fallback `{version}-1`) before build and revert the version in metadata if build fails\n\n#### Requirement: `publish` command\nThe system SHALL publish/deploy using provider `agentcube` (AgentRuntime CR) or `k8s` (Deployment + NodePort Service), preparing the image via Docker push or explicit image URL as implemented in `PublishRuntime`.\n\n##### Scenario: Options and defaults\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `publish`\n- **THEN** defaults SHALL include: `workspace` = `\".\"`; `version` = `None` (`--version`); `image_url` = `None` (`--image-url`); `image_username` = `None` (`--image-username`); `image_password` = `None` (`--image-password`); `description` = `None`; `region` = `None` (`--region`); `cloud_provider` = `None`; `provider` = `\"agentcube\"` (`--provider`); `node_port` = `None` (`--node-port`, `Optional[int]`); `replicas` = `None` (`--replicas`); `namespace` = `None` (`--namespace`); `verbose` = `False`\n\n##### Scenario: AgentCube provider prerequisites\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `agentcube`\n- **WHEN** metadata lacks `router_url` or `workload_manager_url`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message requiring both fields in `agent_metadata.yaml`\n\n##### Scenario: Standard Kubernetes publish flow\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `k8s` and Kubernetes client initializes\n- **WHEN** publish proceeds\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent`, then `wait_for_deployment_ready(..., timeout=120)`, updating metadata with deployment info; on readiness failure it SHALL raise `RuntimeError` after recording error in metadata\n\n#### Requirement: `invoke` command\nThe system SHALL POST JSON to the published agent endpoint, parse `--payload` as JSON, merge optional `--header` entries, and for AgentRuntime CR deployments rewrite the URL to `{base}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/` when `k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\"`.\n\n##### Scenario: Options and defaults\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `invoke`\n- **THEN** defaults SHALL be: `workspace` = `\".\"`; `payload` = `\"{}\"` (`--payload`, `str`); `header_list` = `None` (`--header`, repeatable `List[str]`); `provider` = `\"agentcube\"`; `verbose` = `False`\n\n##### Scenario: Invalid payload\n- **GIVEN** `payload` is not valid JSON\n- **WHEN** the command parses it\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print invalid JSON in red and exit with code `1` (before `_handle_error`)\n\n##### Scenario: Invalid header format\n- **GIVEN** a header string without a single `:` separator\n- **WHEN** headers are parsed\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print expected `key:value` format and exit with code `1`\n\n##### Scenario: Session header on invoke\n- **GIVEN** metadata contains `session_id`\n- **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime.invoke` runs\n- **THEN** the HTTP client SHALL add header `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` (same spelling as response handling) to the request\n\n#### Requirement: `status` command\nThe system SHALL load workspace metadata and display agent status in a Rich `Table`, exiting with code `1` when status is `not_published` or `error`.\n\n##### Scenario: Options and defaults\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `status`\n- **THEN** defaults SHALL be: `workspace` = `\".\"`; `provider` = `\"agentcube\"`; `verbose` = `False`\n\n##### Scenario: Not published\n- **GIVEN** metadata has no `agent_id`\n- **WHEN** `get_status` returns `status == \"not_published\"`\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print guidance to publish first and exit with code `1`\n\n#### Requirement: Workspace validation (pack path)\nThe system SHALL validate that the workspace path exists and is a directory; for Python, require at least one `*.py` file; for Java, require `pom.xml`.\n\n##### Scenario: Missing workspace\n- **GIVEN** `workspace_path` does not exist\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_workspace_structure` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with a message that the directory does not exist\n\n##### Scenario: Python workspace without Python files\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.language == \"python\"`\n- **WHEN** no `*.py` exists in the workspace root\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")`\n\n#### Requirement: Metadata file format\nThe system SHALL persist agent configuration as YAML. The primary filename SHALL be `agent_metadata.yaml`; loading SHALL fall back to `agent.yaml` then `metadata.yaml` if the primary file is missing.\n\n##### Scenario: Save location\n- **GIVEN** metadata is saved\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.save_metadata` runs\n- **THEN** the file SHALL be written to `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml` using `yaml.dump` with `default_flow_style=False`, `indent=2`, `sort_keys=False`, excluding `None` fields via `model_dump(exclude_none=True)`\n\n##### Scenario: Schema validation\n- **GIVEN** YAML is loaded\n- **WHEN** fields violate `AgentMetadata` validators\n- **THEN** Pydantic SHALL reject unsupported `language` / `build_mode` or invalid `port` range\n\n#### Requirement: Docker integration\nThe system SHALL use the Docker SDK (`docker.from_env()`) to build images, push to a registry when configured, and optionally remove images.\n\n##### Scenario: Build image\n- **GIVEN** Docker is running\n- **WHEN** `DockerService.build_image` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL tag `{image_name}:{tag}`, pass optional `buildargs` from proxy settings, and return `image_name`, `image_id`, `image_size`, `build_time`\n\n##### Scenario: Push image\n- **GIVEN** a local image name and optional `registry_url` / credentials\n- **WHEN** `DockerService.push_image` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL login if username and password are provided, retag when needed, stream push logs, and return `pushed_image` and `push_time`\n\n##### Scenario: Remove image\n- **GIVEN** `DockerService.remove_image(image_name)` is called\n- **WHEN** removal succeeds\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `True`; on failure it SHALL log a warning and return `False`\n\n#### Requirement: Kubernetes — standard provider\nThe system SHALL create or patch `Deployment` and `NodePort` `Service`, wait for rollout, report pod status, and support deletion.\n\n##### Scenario: Deploy agent\n- **GIVEN** `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent` is called\n- **WHEN** resources are applied\n- **THEN** the result SHALL include `deployment_name`, `service_name`, `namespace`, `replicas`, `container_port`, `node_port`, `service_url` as `http://localhost:{node_port}`\n\n##### Scenario: Wait for ready\n- **GIVEN** a deployment name\n- **WHEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready` exceeds `timeout` seconds (default `120`)\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `TimeoutError`\n\n##### Scenario: Delete agent\n- **GIVEN** `delete_agent` is called\n- **WHEN** deletion completes\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `{\"status\": \"deleted\", \"deployment_name\", \"namespace\"}` ignoring 404 on individual deletes\n\n#### Requirement: Kubernetes — AgentCube AgentRuntime CR\nThe system SHALL create or patch an `AgentRuntime` custom object in group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, version `v1alpha1`, plural `agentruntimes`.\n\n##### Scenario: Deploy CR\n- **GIVEN** required readiness probe fields exist in metadata\n- **WHEN** `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL embed `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` / `ROUTER_URL` from parameters or environment when missing in `env_vars`, set `sessionTimeout` to `\"15m\"` and `maxSessionDuration` to `\"8h\"`, and reference `imagePullSecrets` `[{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}]`\n\n#### Requirement: AgentCube provider integration (CLI)\nThe system SHALL use `AgentCubeProvider` for `provider=agentcube` publish/status flows and `KubernetesProvider` for `provider=k8s`.\n\n##### Scenario: Status for AgentRuntime\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `agentcube` and the CR exists\n- **WHEN** `StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status` runs\n- **THEN** status SHALL be read from `cr_object[\"status\"]` when present (`status`, `agentEndpoint`), else `created_no_status`, else `not_found_in_k8s`\n\n#### Requirement: Error handling patterns\nThe system SHALL use `_handle_error(e, command_name, verbose)` for subcommand exceptions: print `Error {command_name}: {e}` in red; if `verbose`, print traceback; raise `typer.Exit(1)`.\n\n##### Scenario: Subcommand verbose vs global verbose\n- **GIVEN** a subcommand's local `--verbose` is `True` but global `-v` was not passed\n- **WHEN** an error occurs in that subcommand\n- **THEN** traceback SHALL still be printed because `_handle_error` receives the subcommand's `verbose` flag\n\n---\n\n## 10. Client-Go Library\n\nGenerated Kubernetes client code for API group **`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` / `v1alpha1`**, module path **`github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`**. Source reference: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`.\n\n### Clientset\n\n#### `Interface` (`clientset/versioned/clientset.go`)\n\n```go\ntype Interface interface {\n\tDiscovery() discovery.DiscoveryInterface\n\tRuntimeV1alpha1() runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n}\n```\n\n#### `Clientset` struct\n\nEmbeds `*discovery.DiscoveryClient` and holds `runtimeV1alpha1 *runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Client`.\n\n**Constructors**\n\n- `NewForConfig(c *rest.Config) (*Clientset, error)`\n- `NewForConfigAndClient(c *rest.Config, httpClient *http.Client) (*Clientset, error)`\n- `NewForConfigOrDie(c *rest.Config) *Clientset`\n- `New(c rest.Interface) *Clientset`\n\n**Group accessor:** `RuntimeV1alpha1() runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface`\n\n---\n\n### Typed client — `runtime/v1alpha1`\n\n#### `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface` (`clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/runtime_client.go`)\n\n```go\ntype RuntimeV1alpha1Interface interface {\n\tRESTClient() rest.Interface\n\tAgentRuntimesGetter\n\tCodeInterpretersGetter\n}\n```\n\n`RuntimeV1alpha1Client` implements this interface. REST defaults: `GroupVersion` = `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`.SchemeGroupVersion, `APIPath` = `/apis`, negotiated serializer from `clientset/versioned/scheme`.\n\n#### `AgentRuntimesGetter` / `AgentRuntimeInterface` (`.../agentruntime.go`)\n\n```go\ntype AgentRuntimesGetter interface {\n\tAgentRuntimes(namespace string) AgentRuntimeInterface\n}\n\ntype AgentRuntimeInterface interface {\n\tCreate(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.CreateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n\tUpdate(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n\tUpdateStatus(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n\tDelete(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.DeleteOptions) error\n\tDeleteCollection(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.DeleteOptions, listOpts metav1.ListOptions) error\n\tGet(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.GetOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n\tList(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeList, error)\n\tWatch(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (watch.Interface, error)\n\tPatch(ctx context.Context, name string, pt types.PatchType, data []byte, opts metav1.PatchOptions, subresources ...string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n\tAgentRuntimeExpansion\n}\n```\n\nREST resource plural: **`agentruntimes`**.\n\n#### `CodeInterpretersGetter` / `CodeInterpreterInterface` (`.../codeinterpreter.go`)\n\nSame method shape as `AgentRuntimeInterface`, types `*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter` / `CodeInterpreterList`. REST resource plural: **`codeinterpreters`**.\n\n#### Expansion hooks (`generated_expansion.go`)\n\n```go\ntype AgentRuntimeExpansion interface{}\ntype CodeInterpreterExpansion interface{}\n```\n\n(Empty — reserved for custom methods.)\n\n#### Fake clients (`typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/`)\n\n`fake_runtime_client.go`, `fake_agentruntime.go`, `fake_codeinterpreter.go` — test doubles implementing the typed interfaces; `doc.go` markers.\n\n---\n\n### Scheme (`clientset/versioned/scheme/`)\n\n| File | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `register.go` | Builds `Scheme`, `Codecs`, `ParameterCodec`; `AddToScheme` registers `runtime/v1alpha1` types |\n| `doc.go` | Package doc |\n\n---\n\n### Informer factory\n\n#### `SharedInformerFactory` (`informers/externalversions/factory.go`)\n\n```go\ntype SharedInformerFactory interface {\n\tinternalinterfaces.SharedInformerFactory\n\tStart(stopCh <-chan struct{})\n\tShutdown()\n\tWaitForCacheSync(stopCh <-chan struct{}) map[reflect.Type]bool\n\tForResource(resource schema.GroupVersionResource) (GenericInformer, error)\n\tInformerFor(obj runtime.Object, newFunc internalinterfaces.NewInformerFunc) cache.SharedIndexInformer\n\tRuntime() externalversionsruntime.Interface\n}\n```\n\n**Constructors / options**\n\n- `NewSharedInformerFactory(client versioned.Interface, defaultResync time.Duration)`\n- `NewSharedInformerFactoryWithOptions(client, defaultResync, options ...SharedInformerOption)`\n- `NewFilteredSharedInformerFactory` (deprecated alias to WithOptions)\n- Options: `WithCustomResyncConfig`, `WithTweakListOptions`, `WithNamespace`, `WithTransform`\n\n### Group interface (`informers/externalversions/runtime/interface.go`)\n\n```go\ntype Interface interface {\n\tV1alpha1() v1alpha1.Interface\n}\n```\n\n`New(factory, namespace, tweakListOptions)` returns group accessor.\n\n### Version interface (`informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/interface.go`)\n\n```go\ntype Interface interface {\n\tAgentRuntimes() AgentRuntimeInformer\n\tCodeInterpreters() CodeInterpreterInformer\n}\n```\n\n### Per-type informers (`.../runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go`, `codeinterpreter.go`)\n\nExample (`AgentRuntimeInformer`):\n\n```go\ntype AgentRuntimeInformer interface {\n\tInformer() cache.SharedIndexInformer\n\tLister() runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeLister\n}\n```\n\nAlso provides `NewAgentRuntimeInformer`, `NewFilteredAgentRuntimeInformer`, and analogous constructors for CodeInterpreter.\n\n### Generic resource routing (`informers/externalversions/generic.go`)\n\n`ForResource` switches on:\n\n- `v1alpha1.SchemeGroupVersion.WithResource(\"agentruntimes\")` → `f.Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes().Informer()`\n- `...WithResource(\"codeinterpreters\")` → `...CodeInterpreters().Informer()`\n\n### `internalinterfaces` (`informers/externalversions/internalinterfaces/factory_interfaces.go`)\n\n```go\ntype NewInformerFunc func(versioned.Interface, time.Duration) cache.SharedIndexIn